title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat after each one.
Add pineapple.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until light brown.

title: 14-carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.

title: alma's almond pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar until very light and fluffy; add flavorings.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add alternately the flour and baking powder with milk beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured tube cake pan at 325°
for 1 1/2 hours, or in gas oven at 300°
for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not open oven door before 1 hour.

title: avocado salsa
directions: In large bowl, mix corn, olives, red bell pepper and onion. In small bowl, mix garlic, olive oil, lemon juice, vinegar, oregano, salt and pepper. Pour into corn mixture and toss to coat. Cover and chill in the refrigerator 8 hours or overnight. Stir avocados into the mixture before serving.

title: kentucky corn
directions: Put all ingredients in a dish and stir together.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes for a long, glass pan or 45 minutes in a round glass dish.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Pour into pie crust (graham cracker or regular); cook 8 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip after pie has cooled; refrigerate.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Rub steak with salt and pepper.
Pound all the flour possible into steak.
Sear on both sides in hot cooking oil.
Lower heat and cook until browned.
Very good and easy to cook.

title: pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press cream cheese in bottom of 9-inch glass pie pan.
Spread pizza sauce over cream cheese.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed.
Bake for 25 minutes. Serve with corn chips.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put chicken in a very large casserole dish or a covered roasting pan.
Add all ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: easy vegetable bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased 2 qt. casserole.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Heat oil and add meat, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Cook until meat is browned and onion is translucent.
Drain excess oil. Then add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes over low to medium heat.
While sauce is simmering, cook a 12 ounce package of spaghetti noodles to desired tenderness.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti and top with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes about 5 large servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice
zucchini
into bacon grease along with onion and green pepper.
Fry until tender, about 5 minutes.
Season with salt, pepper
and garlic.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Pour into casserole dish and top with crumbled bacon and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Scramble egg in skillet with oil, stirring to break into pieces.
Add water, soy sauce, garlic and onion; bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork before serving.

title: diabetic buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and jello and bring to a boil.
Add buttermilk. Gradually add beaten topping and pour into a 9 x 12-inch dish. Sprinkle nuts over the top.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze while chocolate melts.

title: sauerkraut, beans and potatoes
directions: Put beans and drained sauerkraut in pan with 1 1/2 cups water. While cooking, fry about 4 slices of bacon (cut in small pieces). When crisp, add to sauerkraut and beans and let cook.
Peel and dice potatoes in small pieces, boil until soft, drain water and add to sauerkraut and beans.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer.
Fill up with regular milk.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water; let set 10 minutes.
Put dough hook on mixer and add the next ingredients.
Add yeast.
Mix in flour, a little at a time, until stiff.
Turn into oiled pan and let rise 1 hour.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Make out into rolls; let rise.
Cook at 350°. Makes about 35.

title: shrimp gravy
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and remove from pan.
Saute onions in bacon drippings; do not brown.
Add well drained shrimp, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
After shrimp turn pink, sprinkle in flour until consistency which pleases you.
Crumble bacon and add.
Simmer no longer than 5 minutes after adding flour.
Correct seasonings, if necessary.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach, then drain all water out.
Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls 1 inch in diameter.
Bake at 300° for 15 or 20 minutes.
Freeze or refrigerate for 1 or 2 days.
Heat in microwave to warm.
Yields 60 to 70 balls.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Peel and shred coarsely.
Heat butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add the cheese to the butter.
Stir until partially melted.
Blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold this mixture into potatoes.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole dish; dot with butter.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3 day icebox coconut cake
directions: Make 2 to 3 layers of cake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: graham pie crust
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Place in Ziploc bag and roll with rolling pin until small crumbs.
Combine all ingredients and pat into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 7 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar on medium-high heat to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Beat until smooth and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: shrimp ceviche
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Flavor reaches its peak in about 3 hours.

title: e z chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Pour broth, soup, chicken and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a large pot.
Add water to desired level of broth.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Mix together flour, salt, pepper and buttermilk.
Increase or decrease amount of flour to get a fluffy consistency.

title: "porcanoo"(pork, cabbage and noodles)
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Shred cabbage, carrot, celery and onion or cut into small pieces.
Cut meat into small pieces. Brown meat in skillet with very little oil.
Add garlic and lightly brown it.
Add water and bring to a boil on medium heat. When meat is tender, add carrot, cabbage and celery.
Bring to boil, adding a little more water if needed.
Add rest of ingredients, including cooked noodles.
Cook slowly, stirring all ingredients together.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add sugar to taste.
Makes 25 cups.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place thin sliced potatoes and onion in baking dish.
Make mixture from other ingredients and pour over potatoes and onions. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese, both sugars, and vanilla.
Add peanuts.
Cut apples into slices and use for dipping.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough and separate into 8 triangles. On a large round stone or pizza pan, arrange in a circle with points in the center and wide ends on the outside. Press seams together to seal.
Bake 12-15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
Can also be made on an oblong pan or stone.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic and dill weed.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Prepare veggies by dicing or slicing into small pieces and sprinkle over pizza.
Cut into triangles or squares.
10 servings.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray; add oil and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute for 3 minutes or until tender.
Stir in tomato and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix corn, rice, soup and butter.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: country sausage, potatoes au gratin casserole
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion in oil until onion is tender. Stir in potatoes, sauce, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to simmer.
Now stir in carrots; cover and simmer again 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and cheese; cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Good dish to make when camping.

title: coconut pie
directions: Scald 2 cups milk.
Combine flour, cornstarch, sugar, salt and egg yolks and 1 cup milk.
Mix and add to scalded milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and coconut.
Put into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake until brown.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and beaten eggs in a double boiler; stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add butter.
When cool, fold in remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: best meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except ketchup. Spread on ungreased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake uncovered 1 to 1 1/4 hours, spooning ketchup over top of meat loaf during last 15 minutes of baking.
Serves 8.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; reserve 2 teaspoons sugar for topping.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to wet ingredients.
Pour into muffin tins.
Sprinkle with sugar topping.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten egg, then mix sour milk and molasses together, alternately with dry ingredients, sifted together.
Pour into a greased and floured shallow pan.
Bake 45 minutes in a modern oven at 400°.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, vinegar and cream of tartar for 5 minutes only; do not let boil over.
Let cool.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: This is so easy, I am almost embarrassed to submit it.
But for someone who works and has little time, it is a real blessing.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in butter and oil mixture.
Add ground beef; brown until done.
Drain excess grease.
Add water, rice and bouillon cubes.
Stir; cover and let simmer on low heat until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Layer top of rice with sliced tomato.
Top with shredded cheese while cheese is hot.
Cover until melted.

title: diana's baked beans
directions: Brown bacon. Saute chopped onion in some of the bacon grease. Mix all ingredients together. Place in 13 x 9 baking dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: johnnie mazetti
directions: Brown onion and hamburger; drain.
Boil noodles until soft; drain.
Combine soups in saucepan and heat.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix together sugar, Miracle Whip and salt.
Sift together flour, cocoa and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Add lukewarm water and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cheese.
Blend ingredients.
Roll into 2 balls and coat with chopped walnuts.

title: grand glorious red punch
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1-cup boiling water.
Stir in frozen lemonade or pineapple-orange juice.
Add cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
In large punch bowl, place 2 trays of ice cubes or a molded ice ring.
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Fruit flavored sherbet may be added, if desired.
Makes about 25 servings.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Heat
all ingredients, except parsley, in saucepan.
Do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cream of split pea soup
directions: Pick over peas; cover with cold water and soak overnight. Drain.
Add cold water, ham pieces, onion and carrots.
Simmer 4 hours or until peas and vegetables are tender.
Melt butter; add flour and stir to make a smooth paste.
Add pepper, salt and milk. If too thick, add more milk.
(If the celery is added, it should be put in during the last hour of cooking.)
Garnish with croutons and toasted almond slices if desired.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare eggplant; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Cook in small amount of water until tender (cook until all water is absorbed).
Brown sausage and onion; add with eggs and bread crumbs to partially cooled eggplant.
Stir together and put into a greased baking dish.
Cover with the 1/2 cup of buttered cracker crumbs and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, leaving out 1/2 of Cheddar to sprinkle over top.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 450° until done.
Um Um good.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half (lengthwise) and cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes around 1 or more loaves of bread.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cook tomatoes and bread until quite thick.
Add sugar, margarine, salt and pepper. Turn into a buttered 8-cup casserole. Bake in 350° oven, uncovered, one hour or more.
Pudding should be glazed and brown on top.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in large tube pan.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Pour 2 tablespoons margarine in pan. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar and peanuts evenly over bottom of pan. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over mixture.
Beat egg at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat well.
Add peanut butter and 2 tablespoons margarine, mixing well.
Add buttermilk, mixing until blended.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool on a wire rack.

title: pineapple and cheese bake
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges; save juice.
Put pineapple, oranges and cheese in mixing dish.
Mix cornstarch and sugar and liquids from fruit in a saucepan.
Cook until thickened and pour over pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Wash rice.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks and boil in salted water until tender.
Drain, then mash until all lumps are gone.
Stir in cream cheese and sour cream until well blended.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook ground beef with diced onion until brown, then add tomato juice, water, red hot chili beans, salt and chili powder.
(I add my chili powder to the meat first and then add rest of ingredients.)
Allow this to cook until it thickens (about 45 minutes to 1 hour), then add macaroni and continue to cook until macaroni is done.

title: ruby's crazy crunch
directions: Bring to boil sugar, margarine, vanilla and syrup.
Pour over popcorn and nuts and put on cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart.

title: lois' chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Mix flour and soda and add alternately with chocolate syrup. Blend in vanilla. Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan for about 35 to 40 minutes. Frost while warm with chocolate frosting.

title: easy custard frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and blend.
Beat with mixer until custardy.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender for 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350° in a greased pie plate.
Easy! Makes its own crust!

title: sausage supreme
directions: Cut sausage in small sections.
Brown in skillet; drain grease.
Peel and slice potatoes and onion, about 1/4-inch thick rounds.
Place first 3 ingredients in a large pot.
Pour tomato soup and 1/2 can water over ingredients.
Cover with a tight lid; bring to a good steam and lower temperature to simmer.
Let simmer for 25 to
30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Very good with cabbage slaw on the side.

title: old kentucky apple pecan cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to wet mixture.
Fold in pecans and chopped apples. Add vanilla.
Start in cold oven.
Set oven at 325° and bake 1 hour.
Pour frosting over hot cake.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, chocolate mix, salt and soda.
Stir in creamed mixture, alternate with milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes; let stand on cookie sheet 2 to 3 minutes before removing.
Fill with icing.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zippy hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain, chop and mix ingredients.
Microwave 5 minutes or until hot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, oleo, and sugars.
Add water, eggs, and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add flour, salt, and soda.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until mixed well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: prayer cookies
directions: Write prayer requests on small strips of paper and fold them into small pieces.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter; mix avocado, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Spread over bean dip. Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread, then layer of onions, layer of olives and layer of tomatoes. Grate cheese and put on top. Serve with favorite chips.

title: country raisin gingersnaps
directions: Cream
together
shortening and sugar.	Beat in egg and molasses.
Sift
together flour, soda, salt and spices and add to creamed
mixture.
Mix
in	raisins.
Chill
dough for 1/2 hour. Roll
into	1-inch	balls and roll in additional sugar. Place 2-inches
apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and season to taste.
Slice potatoes and carrots and chop onions.
Add peas.
Add this to hamburger; pour mushroom soup over all.
Add some milk to mix better.
Put into casserole bowl and bake at 350° for about 2 hours; check for doneness.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add milk, shortening, salt, sugar and eggs. Stir in flour slowly. Mix until dough is formed. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. Make into rolls. Place in pan and let rise. Bake at 425° until done.

title: raisin filled cake
directions: This will be moist crumbs.
Pat 3/4 of this mixture in bottom of a greased and floured cake pan.
Pour filling over this and add remaining crumbs on top.

title: "super bowl" scallop casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add Ritz cracker crumbs, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Fold scallops in.
Place in ungreased casserole dish.
Pour heavy cream over evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, cream cheese and milk together and whip with blender. May use any kind of fruit to dip in mixture. If using apples, soak them in pineapple juice first.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt peanut butter and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until blended.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Break cream cheese up into undiluted tomato soup in saucepan.
Heat (stirring) until cheese melts. Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add celery, onions and shrimp to tomato mixture.
Add gelatin mixture; stir well.
Pour into 5 1/2 cup mold and refrigerate.

title: bohemian biscuits
directions: Mix together, sprinkle top of dough with flour.
Cover and store in refrigerator for three days.
Remove and bake desired amount.
Return balance to refrigerate.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add dates and put all in skillet with butter.
Cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add black walnuts and Rice Krispies.
Let cool a little. Work together with greased hands.
Make into a roll, then roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice as needed.
(Better double the recipe as they are sooooo good.)

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: santa fe potato salad
directions: In large saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water to cover until tender, about 40 minutes; drain.
Cool slightly; cut into cubes.
In small bowl, combine oil, vinegar and taco spices.
Add to warm potatoes and toss gently to coat.
Cover; refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Gently fold in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: mock whipped cream
directions: Cook flour and milk in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour into a dish and cool.
In a small bowl, cream the butter and shortening with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Add sugar gradually, beating another 4 minutes.
Add the flour paste; beat 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend.
Makes enough for one layer cake.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange in layers in baking dish.
Melt margarine, cut bread into 9 pieces.
Dip bread on both sides in margarine.
Lay on top, sprinkle cheese on top of bread.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees. (Use 8 x 8 pan.)

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli, bacon bits and onion in a bowl. Mix mayonnaise, wine vinegar and sugar together. Pour over broccoli. Let sit overnight.

title: squash and sausage casserole
directions: Cook and slice squash; drain.
Mix sausage, beaten egg, crackers, evaporated milk and 8 ounces of the cheese.
Mix and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of the cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sleeping cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites at high until frothy; add salt.
Continue to beat.
Add sugar, some at a time, beating all the while.
Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla, still beating. Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet, even if Teflon.
Put batter on sheet using heaping teaspoonful.
Put in oven.
Turn it off.
Take a nap while they are baking; read a good book.
Just leave cookies alone for at least 3 hours.
They freeze well and thaw quickly.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Skin tomatoes; coarsely chop in large bowl.
Combine tomatoes, juice, cucumbers, onion, pepper, garlic, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Chill and serve.

title: two-tomato salad
directions: In a large bowl with wire whisk or fork, beat chopped basil, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and sugar until blended.
Set dressing aside.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and place in greased baking dish.
In a small pan, melt 1/4 cup butter and cheese, stirring often.
Add soup and dill weed.
Pour over carrots.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and toss with crackers.
Place on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice onion over all ribs and bake 1/2 hour.
Mix sauce ingredients together and spread over all ribs. Turn oven down to 350° and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and cut apples into small pieces.
Place in baking dish. Cream oleo and sugar together. Mix eggs, vanilla and nuts into this mixture.
Spread over top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; cook in boiling water with onions for 5 minutes. Mix sour cream and mushroom soup with carrots.
Fold into cooked, drained squash.
Add melted butter (or margarine) to stuffing mix. Line baking dish with this mixture, reserving some for topping. Pour squash mixture into this lined baking dish; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tomato gravy
directions: Fry onion until light brown; add flour and brown.
Add the tomatoes and then strain all in pan and add the salt and sugar. Cook about 5 minutes until thick.
This gravy is good with beef meat from soup and potatoes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda and salt and sift again. Add enough sour cream to form a soft dough. Turn onto floured board. Knead slightly. Roll 1/2-inch thick. Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Bake in hot oven (500°) 15 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: country style mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until cooked.
Drain water.
Add evaporated milk and mash with fork.
Then mix with blender on whip.
Add butter; whip until creamy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in a bowl; garnish with fresh parsley.

title: turkey breasts
directions: Make stuffing according to package directions.
Put stuffing onto each slice of turkey.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
In a shallow pan put 1/2 of the gravy.
Lay each turkey roll in gravy and put remaining gravy on top.
Place into a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: fluffy brandy sauce
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Beat in egg yolk and salt.
Fold all into whipped cream and brandy.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.

title: crunchy pears
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spray pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inches), with nonstick cooking spray. Carefully pare pears, leaving stems attached; place on large plate.
Mix orange juice and marmalade; spoon over pears.
Mix wafer crumbs and almonds.
Roll pears in crumb mixture; stand upright in pie plate.
Mix yogurt and remaining sauce from plate; refrigerate.
Bake pears 35 to 45 minutes or until tender when pierced with a fork (baking time may vary due to size of pears). Serve warm with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix juice, lemon juice and milk real good.
Add Cool Whip. Add fruit and mix in well.
Refrigerate.

title: easy blender quiche(serves 6)
directions: *May substitute shrimp, vegetables, ham, etc.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in bowl.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to egg mixture along with nuts and fruit cocktail. Beat well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While still warm, add topping.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup cake mix. Add butter and egg to remaining mix.
Press into pan.
Prepare filling.
Combine pumpkin, eggs and milk until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Combine reserved cake mix with 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: oyster stew
directions: Remove any pieces of shell from oysters but do not wash.
Melt butter in saucepan; drop oyster in and cook until oysters begin to curl at the edges.
Add salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Scald milk and combine with the oysters.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple ham casserole
directions: Combine 1 1/3 cups precooked rice in a saucepan with soup and water.
Add cubed ham, celery, onion and peas.
Heat to boiling. Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and arrange pineapple slices on top.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: olivia's favorite grilled cheese
directions: Put 1 tsp. oleo in frying pan (small).
Melt oleo.
Place slice of cheese between slices of bread.
Put small amounts of oleo on top slice of bread.
Put in fryer and brown on both sides.

title: chicken liver pat{2e
directions: Melt
small
amount of butter in saucepan.
Add livers. Cook, covered,
until no longer pink.
Put through food mill. Mix livers with the juices and other ingredients.
Put in dish and chill for several hours.

title: easy modeling clay
directions: Mix flour, salt and cornstarch in bowl.
Add warm water gradually until mixture forms a shape.
Knead.
Can be used to make beads, shapes, etc.
Air dry.
Paint and seal, if desired.

title: cheese sauce for vegetables
directions: Microwave butter in a 2 cup glass measuring cup on High for 30 to 60 seconds until melted.
Add flour and salt; stir until a smooth paste forms.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until blended and smooth.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring twice, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 1 cup.
Per 1/4 cup:
135 calories.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and salt.
Beat until peaks form.
Add flavoring and chocolate bits.
Fold until well mixed.
Cover cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Do not make too big.
Batter expands.
Place in oven; turn oven off! Leave overnight in oven.
If made in daytime, leave in oven at least 4 hours.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: large moist jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Sprinkle, then toss, with mixture of cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Measure and mix in order the rest of the ingredients.
Grease and dust with flour a large (10-inch) tube pan.
Put half the cake mixture in the pan; cover with half the apple mixture.
Add rest of batter; top with remaining apple mixture.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: holiday eggnog punch
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Pour into punch bowl.
Hang small candy canes around bowl.

title: ham and potato breakfast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except paprika, in large bowl.
Pour into ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 17 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: kim's barbecued steak and potatoes
directions: Put steaks and potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour remainder of ingredients over and cover with foil.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix soups and set aside.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Butter a casserole dish and put half of the Tater Tots on bottom.
Drain off grease from meat and put on top of Tater Tots.
Add remaining Tater Tots on top of meat.
Pour soup mixtures on top and bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: zucchini bread or cake
directions: In a large bowl mix all ingredients except eggs and oil.
In another bowl, beat eggs and oil.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then invert on rack and cool completely.
Sprinkle a little confectioners sugar on top.

title: amish dessert
directions: Boil water, sugar and tapioca until clear.
Stir in jello powder.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip and strawberries.
Any flavor of jello and fruit may be substituted.

title: crunchy fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip into beaten egg and then in crumbs.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add tomato slices and cook until brown on each side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: charcoaled corned beef
directions: Spoon vinegar over brisket.
Place in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle brisket with garlic powder, salt and pepper on all sides. Marinate at room temperature for several hours, turning occasionally (example:
10 a.m. to 6 p.m.).
Cook on charcoal grill with top closed for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or use thermometer to register rare.
Do not overcook!
Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.
Return to butcher to have thinly sliced.
Serve with party rye and hot mustard.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 13 casserole dish.
Add flour and mix to form a crust on the bottom of dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until light brown.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, 1/2 of Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top pudding layer with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes. May be frozen before baking, baked without thawing at the same time they are used or baked frozen and reheated at serving time.
Makes 150 to 175 balls.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl combine cake mix, margarine, eggs and water; mix well (dough will be stiff).
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool 2 minutes on cookie sheet.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers (do not peel). Soak cucumber

slices and chopped onions in salt water to cover for 4 hours. Drain and rinse thoroughly. Mix other ingredients and add to cucumbers. Boil 20 minutes (stir occasionally so they won't burn) and can. Enjoy!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Sift together dry ingredients and add to the zucchini mixture. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook roast. Chop into small pieces. Add water for egg noodles. Add bouillon cubes. Cook until noodles are done.
Add brown gravy. Cook until thick. Serve.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and almond extract.
Add flour, cocoa and baking soda; beat well.
Set aside.
Prepare yellow cake mix batter according to directions on box; pour half into bottom of prepared pan.
Spoon cocoa batter in dollops over yellow cake batter; top with remaining yellow cake batter and cherry pie filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center of cake is firm.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Garnish with additional cherry pie filling, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in butter and roll in cheese and bread crumbs until completely coated.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: dilled broccoli and carrot
directions: In 3-quart microwavable casserole dish, combine onions, carrots and 2 tablespoons water.
Cover tightly with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until onions are tender.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place two kinds of cheese in a bowl and let soften at room temperature.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion; mix.
Form a ball.
Sprinkle nuts on the ball. Wrap ball in plastic.
Wrap until ready to use.
Double if needed.

title: golden punch
directions: Combine fruit juices; chill well. Pour over ice in punch bowl. Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish with lemon slices or fresh mint.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Layer in large bowl: brownies, crushed candy bars, mousse and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle leftover crushed candy bars on top of Cool Whip.
Enjoy!!!

title: grilled hawaiian chicken
directions: Marinate fillets in soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce and pineapple juice for about an hour.
Grill with pineapple slices on top until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: For No Bake Cheesecake:
Add 1 (14 ounce) can condensed milk; reduce cream cheese to one package and add 1/3 cup lemon juice. Increase vanilla to 1 teaspoon and do steps 1, 2, 4, 7 and 8.
No sugar, no eggs.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saut onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients except tortilla strips and cheese.
Cook until hot. Place tortilla strips into bowls.
Spoon soup into bowls and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Pour off any fat. Add other ingredients and simmer slowly for 20 minutes. Spoon into sandwich rolls and enjoy.
(Also good on hot dogs.)

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Place cheese in blender until creamy.
Add sugar and beaten eggs, then milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (8-inch).
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Continue baking for 20 minutes more.

title: cobb salad(russian dressing)
directions: Just before serving, assemble salad.
Place lettuce, romaine and chicory in salad bowl.
Arrange tomato and avocado around edge of bowl.
Mound chicken in center and sprinkle with bacon.
Chop egg white and egg yolk separately; sprinkle decoratively, along with chives, over top of salad.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: cider waldorf mold
directions: Bring 1 cup apple cider or juice to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling cider.
Stir in remaining cider or juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apple, celery and pecans.
Pour into a 3-cup mold or spoon into 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm. Unmold on lettuce-line plates.
Serve with mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Serves 6.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well in greased casserole (2 1/2-quart).
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: kentucky cream candy
directions: Stir all ingredients into boiling water.
Cook without stirring over low or medium heat until mixture reaches 250 degrees.
Pour onto a marble slab or onto countertop.
Do not scrape pan.
When cool enough to touch, butter hands, pull candy until mixture is too hard to pull.
(Will be stiff.)

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to directions and place in casserole dish.
Melt butter; add flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Add milk slowly, stirring often as it thickens.
When thick, add 2 cups cheese and stir until melted.
Pour cheese mixture over noodles and mix thoroughly.
I sprinkle more cheese on top.
You can add partially cooked vegetables or various meats to the mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn into a greased deep 10-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° until set or golden brown.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice and sugar. Add pineapple juice. Chill. Add cold ginger ale just before serving. Makes one punch bowl.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sprinkle 4 sheets of waxed paper with powdered sugar.
Melt margarine and chocolate chips.
Mix marshmallows and chopped nuts. Put on wax paper and roll.
Cut in slices and eat.

title: diabetic apple jelly
directions: Soften the gelatin in 1/2 cup of the juice.
Meanwhile, heat the remaining 1 1/2 cups of juice to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the softened gelatin until it is dissolved.
Add artificial sweetener, lemon juice and food coloring.
If you like, return to heat and bring back to boil.
Pour into sterilized jars that have lids.
Store in refrigerator.

title: new orleans red beans and rice
directions: Cook bacon in 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, until brown, but not crisp, about 5 minutes.
Remove bacon from skillet; drain off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onions and garlic to skillet; cook until onions are tender, but not brown, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken and apricot stir-fry
directions: Coat a wok or 10-inch skillet with no-stick spray and toss the garlic on medium-high heat for 30 seconds.
Remove garlic, add chicken and stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add apricots and scallions and stir-fry for 1 minute longer.
Remove chicken and apricots.

title: gingerbread men cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, molasses and vinegar in saucepan. Bring to a boil and let cool.
Re-sift flour together with baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Stir beaten egg into molasses mixture.
Then blend sifted ingredients into molasses mixture. Mix well, then chill dough, covered, in refrigerator.
Break off one-third of the cooled dough; roll out on a lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into gingerbread men.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread dough into pizza shape onto pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: squash muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook squash in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash thoroughly.
Measure 2 cups of squash.
Combine squash, eggs and margarine, stirring well.
Set aside.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and stir in the squash mixture until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins, 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen after baking.
Averages 24 muffins.

title: brown sugar macaroons
directions: Set oven at 250°.
Beat egg white very stiff.
Beat in brown sugar gradually.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper over cookie sheet.
When done, pull paper off onto wet tea towel for a few minutes, then remove cookies.
Bake until done, may take 30 to 45 minutes.
(When one can be lifted off waxed paper, it is done.)
Recipe can be doubled.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Grind, chop or grate meat.
Mix other ingredients with meat and cheese.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Each pie serves 6.
Freezes well after cooking, just reheat.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine all of the vegetables and drain well.
Bring to a boil the oil, vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper.
Cool and pour over vegetables.
Let stand in the refrigerator at least overnight or 24 hours before serving.
This salad will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Serves 10.

title: sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly for 4 days.
On the 5th day, form links and bake at 150° for 10 hours.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients for marinade.
Put flank steak in freezer bag; pour marinade over it, seal bag and freeze.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve starch in a little cold water. Add boiling water and cook until dissolved.
Divide into 3 portions and add a different color to each. Cool. The paint should be the consistency of thick pudding.

title: bit of brie
directions: Spread pecans in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir 2 times.
Add Kahlua and sugar.
Stir well. Remove top rind from cheese.
Place cheese on microwave-safe dish. Spoon pecan mixture over cheese.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: old-fashion meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread, onion, egg, salt and pepper. Add 1/2 of the tomato sauce.
Shape into 12 balls and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: squash delight casserole
directions: Place squash in casserole dish; cover with mixture of remaining ingredients except oleo and dressing mix.
Mix oleo with dressing mix and top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin-pineapple squares
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, pineapple, vanilla and oil.
Mix until well blended.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into 8 x 8 nonstick pan or foil tin.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.
Divide equally into 4 portions.
Makes 4 servings as part of midday meal. Supplement as required.

title: hot spiced cranberry punch
directions: In large saucepan combine all ingredients and simmer uncovered 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve hot.
Serves 50 punch cups.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Combine all ingredients except jello.
Let boil until looks clear and thick.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Let cool.
Add strawberries.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Pour over oatmeal, peanut butter and nuts. Mix together well.
Drop onto waxed paper and let cool.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: sandy's original spaghetti squash casserole
directions: Cut spaghetti squash in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds. Place cut side down in microwave-safe dish and add 2 tablespoons of water to dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove stringy strands of squash from rind and place in ovenproof dish.
Add margarine and Equal and mix thoroughly.
Add juice and pineapple all at once and mix thoroughly.
Top casserole with marshmallows.
Broil on top rack in oven until marshmallows melt and brown a bit.
Remove and smooth marshmallow over entire top; return to broiler and broil until light brown.
Serve immediately.
(Sprinkle with toasted coconut, if desired.)
Serves 4.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved; add orange sherbet, stirring until melted. Add oranges and juice from one can.
Pour into mold and refrigerate.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes.
Slice and layer in baking dish. Pour peach pie filling over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: five baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon and onion until brown, but not crisp.
Add catsup, seasonings and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: pasta with oil and garlic
directions: Cook pasta in large kettle of boiling salted water just until al dente, 6 to 12 minutes.
Drain well.
Keep warm.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Cook all but cornstarch and pineapple juice over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Then add cornstarch and pineapple juice to thicken.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Mix.
Melt butter.
Pour all ingredients into plastic bag. Add melted butter and shake.
Place cut up chicken in bag and shake.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until done.
(Can deep fry.)

title: georgia apple pie
directions: After preparing pastry, mix sugar, flour, spices and salt. Stir in apples.
Place in lined 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust with slits.
Bake until golden brown 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake in covered casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour.
Stir gently when done.

title: uncle bud's green swamp water
directions: Mix all ingredients and add ice.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: cinnamon apple toast
directions: Toast bread lightly on both sides.
Cut in half.
Cream margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Spread on one side of each toasted half.
Cover completely with about 4 apple slices.
Spread margarine-sugar mixture lightly over the apples.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes. Broil for 1 to 2 minutes or until sugar begins to caramelize. Cool slightly and serve immediately.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken and stuffing.
Dip chicken in
mixture.
Let stand overnight.
Roll next day in stuffing. Arrange in single layer in casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Add seasonings to ground beef; brown meat in skillet.
Boil noodles; cut each noodle in half the short way.
Place 2 or 3 tablespoons meat mixture on each noodle; roll up.
Place seam side-down in pan; pour tomato sauce over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix dressing and cream cheese.
Beat with mixer.
Add Cheddar and blend.
Cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape into ball. Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pimiento and three cheeses
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.

title: lobster fettucini
directions: Melt butter in a double boiler and stir in flour to make a roux.
Slowly add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheeses, wine and seasonings; cook until smooth.
Mix lobster meat in and serve over noodles.
Serves 4.

title: pinto bean pie(taste like pecan pie)
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight; rinse and cover with water. Cook beans until tender; mash.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Cream shortening, salt and sugar together.
Put yeast in lukewarm water and melt.
Add scalding water to creamed mixture and melt.
Let cool to lukewarm and add egg and yeast.
Add flour and make soft batter.
Put in refrigerator from 1 to 24 hours.
Take out and make bread or rolls; let rise to double in bulk.
Cook in hot oven (450°) for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country baked ham
directions: Place precooked Virginia ham into deep pan.
Put cloves into ham (across top of ham).
Pour molasses, 7-Up and ginger ale over the ham.
(Use to baste and for a sauce later.)
Place sliced pineapple over the top of ham and pour juice over the ham.
Place into oven and bake for approximately 3 hours at 450° (use a meat thermometer, set for cooked ham) to assure the meat is heated through.
Take out of oven and set for 10 minutes, then slice. Serve with sauce over ham or in a gravy dish (heat sauce).

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, using only 1/2 cup of the chopped pecans.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in wax paper or plastic wrap, then in foil.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple-pear dessert pizza
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Add egg; mix until well blended. Add combined oats, flour and spices; mix well.
Spread onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Arrange fruit on batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until fruit is tender.
Cool and cut into wedges.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: danish apple cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 60 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick at 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Beat cream, sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Cream in cream cheese.
Place ladyfingers on bottom of a glass pan.
Add half of batter, then make another layer of ladyfingers.
Add remaining batter, then top with favorite fruit (Solo canned fruit).
Make the day before so cake can sit and chill.

title: red sweet sour cabbage
directions: Mix together the vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Add cabbage and mix well.
Cook 1/2 hour and 5 minutes on high and then on low.
Stir a few times.
Add bay leaf, cloves, onion powder, apples, salt, pepper and sugar.
Brown bacon pieces in skillet; pour over cabbage, including the grease.
Mix well and cook for 1 hour on low.
Let stand a few hours.
Fill your tummy.

title: saucy bars
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add applesauce and sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix and bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool and slice in pan.

title: heavenly fruit cake
directions: Cut
fruits
into
small pieces.
Mix fruits, dates and nuts, then sprinkle with flour until coated; set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, allspice and nutmeg; set aside.
Beat eggs
until fluffy and light.
Add sugar, margarine
and
vanilla; beat until fluffy and creamy.
Stir flour mixture	into
egg mixture;
beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan, spreading
evenly.
Bake in
preheated 225° oven slowly for 2 1/4 hours
or
until done. Cool pan on rack 30 minutes.
Wrap in foil.

title: opal's caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; cool.
Add powdered sugar gradually until right consistency to spread.

title: tuna gravy casserole
directions: To make gravy, mix flour with melted margarine or meat drippings.
(If mixture is not smooth and moist, add more margarine or meat drippings until consistency is right.)
Brown flour mixture, stirring constantly.
Add milk all at once. Continue to stir constantly.
Cook until smooth and thickened. Add tuna and simmer until bubbly.
Serve over biscuits or toast. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: moe's corned beef and cabbage
directions: In large pot, cover beef with water.
Bring to a boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Drain water.
Cover beef water 1 1/2-inches over beef.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add peeled carrots, potatoes and onions.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Add veggies and quartered cabbage last 15 minutes of cooking.
Broth may be tasted before adding vegetables.
If too salty, remove part of water and add new water to your liking of saltiness.

title: good dip
directions: Combine all and refrigerate (it will last a long time).

title: fruited three grain pilaf
directions: Note:
N.B. Health Food Stores carry millet, quinoa, bulgur and dried cherries.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Make peanut butter and cracker sandwiches.
Melt chocolate and dip crackers.
Place on wax paper or greased cookie sheet to dry.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in foil (well buttered).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool, skin and debone.
Cut into strips.

title: lentil patties
directions: Cook together until lentils are very soft and most of the water is absorbed.
Mash or put in the blender.
Cut day old bread in 1/2-inch cubes and stir well into lentils along with 1 whole beaten egg.
The amount of bread needed will vary with the amount of liquid left in lentils.
Start with 4 to 5 slices.
Heat oil in frypan and drop lentil mixture into oil.
Brown on both sides. Serve with tomato sauce on a roll, etc.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients (flour, wheat germ, soda and salt) together.
Cream peanut butter and butter together.
Gradually add sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Add the milk slowly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Store in airtight container.

title: waldorf salad(christmas salad)
directions: Combine and add salad dressing to taste.
Amounts of any ingredients can be changed to suit personal taste.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box.
Add sugar and cranberry sauce. Mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours before serving.

title: nut loaf
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, beating well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: egg supreme
directions: Place bread in bottom of greased baking dish.
Beat eggs; add milk, meat and cheese.
Pour this over bread and refrigerate overnight.

title: algonquin hazelnut soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large saucepan and simmer together gently, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Make the servings small, the soup is rich.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all together, except 7-Up.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: german chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box, but reduce liquid by 1/4 cup.
Add nuts, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
Mix well. Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes or until set.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel.
Add remaining batter.
Bake another 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown hamburger with large onion.
Drain grease.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and chopped onions; drain.
Add soups and sour cream to meat.
Mix well.
Pour into a square baking dish.
Top with biscuits that you have cut in half.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add salt, nutmeg, vanilla and milk. Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° in unbaked pastry. Makes 2 pies.

title: hot dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Mix all other ingredients; simmer for about 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: lynn's and caesar's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve over torn romaine with croutons.

title: ida craver's coconut cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cream thoroughly.
Add half of the flour and half of the milk, beating at low speed until well blended.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat at high speed after each egg.
Now, add rest of baking powder, flour and milk.
Blend in at low speed; mix well.
Pour batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool layers and frost with Buttercream Frosting, putting coconut between layers and on sides.

title: almond crescents
directions: Cream
shortening, sugar and almond extract.
Add flour and salt and mix well.	Chill overnight.
Roll with hands into a pencil shape about 2 1/2-inches long.
Put on a cookie sheet and shape like a crescent.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes. Cool, then roll in 10x sugar.

title: cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter (melted), honey, salt and mustard.
Mix well and pour over hens; bake 1 1/4 hours, basting every 15 minutes until hens are tender and brown.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix ingredients, adding enough flour until dough is workable. Let set overnight for best results.
Makes enough dough for 2 double crust pies.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix egg, sugar, butter, milk and flour together.
Mix well and fold in blueberries.
Bake in cupcake papers in muffin tins at 425° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: quick pilaf
directions: Brown vermicelli in butter on low heat, add salt and pepper to taste.
Remove from heat and add broth.
Return to heat and add rice.
Cook on medium high until comes to boil, lower heat and cook until 95% of broth evaporates.

title: wonderful apple pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, spices and butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
You may use 1 1/2 teaspoons apple pie spice in place of spices, if desired.
Spread 1/3 of this mixture over bottom of unbaked pastry.
Peel apples, core and cut into slices; put in crust.
Spoon remaining sugar and spice mixture over apples.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "dog food" or "puppy chow"
directions: Melt chocolate, oleo and peanut butter in saucepan until completely melted. Place cereal in a large bowl and pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Mix well to coat.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese. Set aside. Layer hash browns, spaghetti sauce and Ricotta cheese in a 9 x 13-inch (greased) casserole dish. Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coating for chicken or pork
directions: Cut all ingredients together with a pastry blender and use mixer or blender to make it the consistency of cornmeal.
Makes 1 quart.
Store in refrigerator.
Replaces commercial "Shake 'N Bake."

title: coconut squares
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and flour.
Put in the bottom of a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at moderate heat.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl of mixer.
Beat until mixture stands in stiff peaks.
Makes a large bowl almost full. Good served on angel food or pound cake with a blob of whipped topping on top.

title: bavarian apple strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large skillet over medium heat, combine undiluted apple juice concentrate and 1 tablespoon sugar. Place over medium heat; bring to a boil.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves; boil 1 to 2 minutes or until thick and syrupy.
Add apples; cook over medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes or until tender but not mushy when pierced with a fork, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in 1 tablespoon amaretti or gingersnap crumbs.
Cool to room temperature.

title: caviar ring
directions: Mix eggs, mayonnaise, anchovy paste and Worcestershire sauce together.
Add gelatin mixture.
Fold in caviar.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: chloe's brown glaze sauce
directions: Mix about 15 minutes over low heat.
Serve over cheesecake or ice cream.
Would also be good over plain cake.

title: perfect cheesecake
directions: Crust: Mix crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted butter. Press evenly into 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip and Italian dressing; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Add additional salad dressing before serving, if desired.
Delicious when served in tomato wedges.

title: fruit and cream fantasy
directions: Place all fruit in freezer bag and freeze.
When ready to serve dessert, remove from freezer.
Place fruit in blender.
Add milk and blend, adding more liquid if too thick and more fruit if too thin.
(Mixture should be consistency of soft ice cream.) Serve in dessert dishes immediately, garnished with fresh strawberries, chopped walnuts, or as desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Drain
juice
from cherries and pineapple.
Add water to make 3/4 cup.
Heat and dissolve Jell-O.
Add Coca-Cola.
Chill until thickened.	Add rest of ingredients.

title: we cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one large bowl and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.
Let cake cool and spread with frosting.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, beaten eggs and milk; mix until blended.
Stir in drained crab, cheese and green onion.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together margarine and 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Put pieces of cooked chicken over stuffing.
Mix together 1 cup broth, cream of chicken soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mandarin peas
directions: Cook tiny green peas according to directions.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat through before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; make a smooth paste of flour and milk. Add eggs, then melted butter and other ingredients.
Pour into buttered dish or casserole.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake in moderate oven until firm like baked custard (45 to 60 minutes). If baked in microwave, bake 15 to 18 minutes on Level 5.
Pan of hot water not necessary in microwave.

title: patio beans and franks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, saute onion in reserved bacon drippings.
Using a slotted spoon, carefully lift onion from skillet and place in a 2-quart casserole.
To casserole add beans, frankfurters, pineapple, brown sugar, chili sauce, bourbon or pineapple juice and coffee granules. Gently stir to throughly mix ingredients.
Sprinkle bacon over the top.
Bake for 1 hour or until beans are bubbly and juice has thickened.
Makes 7 to 8 servings.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients, bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes. Remove bay leaf and serve.
May be frozen.

title: black walnuts, white sage stuffing
directions: In a small pan, boil juniper berries in water and cook 5 minutes (to reduce liquid by half).
Strain through fine sieve to remove berries.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Brown ham in butter and brown sugar.
Pour off drippings.
Add to skillet the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Top vegetables with ham; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter brittle
directions: Put syrup in big pot; add sugar and bring to a boil for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cornflakes.
Make sure all flakes are covered.
Spoon drop onto plastic wrap.
Let set until hard.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, reserving 1/2 c. of confectioners sugar. In a separate bowl, blend bourbon and corn syrup. Combine wet and dry liquids until well blended. Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Spread remaining 1/2 c. of sugar into cookie sheet. Shape dough into balls and roll in sugar. Store in airtight container.

title: lamb shanks
directions: Put some onion and lamb shank in frying pan and saute.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until hot, then pour over meat.
Put in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Cover.

title: ton-katsu (japanese pork cutlets)
directions: Debone pork chops; make small slit around each piece so they don't shrink and roll up.
Tenderize them if you wish.
Massage in salt, pepper and garlic powder into both sides of each pork chop. Roll them in flour, dip in egg liquid and roll into bread crumbs. Let them rest in refrigerator for at least an hour.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Brown pork chops. Remove pork chops from skillet and saute onions.
Spread cooked rice into a large casserole so that it covers the bottom of the dish.
Lay pork chops on top of the rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: granny jo's strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar, salt and flour; boil until thick.
Add jello and cool a few minutes longer.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour over berries in pie crust and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the chopped onion in the margarine.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish.
Place in preheated oven at 350° until bubbly.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Add soup mix, 6 cups water, celery, carrots, tomatoes and juice, potatoes and simmer until tender.
Mix cornstarch with 3/4 cup cold water.
Add cornstarch until stew is to your liking.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Prepare the fruit and soak in fruit juice while you're preparing the rest of the batter.
Cream the butter and add the sugar gradually.
Then add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well, then the nuts and fruit. Pour into three 9 1/4 x 3 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans which have been buttered, lined with wax paper and buttered over the waxed paper.
Bake in a 275° to 300° oven for 2 to 2 1/4 hours.
Remove from pan immediately.
Cool on cake racks.
Wrap in foil.
Yields 8 pounds.

title: pop over pizza
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Spread mixture into a greased oblong pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Set aside. Beat together until lumps are gone:
egg, milk, flour, oil and salt.
Pour over beef mixture and top with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and margarine over low heat; add vanilla.
Combine sugar and cocoa in large bowl.
Add cheese and margarine mixture to sugar and cocoa.
Blend well until lumps are smooth.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread into pan.
Place in refrigerator to cool.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Drain tomatoes; save juice.
Mix meat, tomatoes, onion, 1 clove garlic, rice, salt and pepper.
Roll into 2-inch long rolls. Remove cabbage leaves and boil until wilted.
Roll meat rolls into cabbage leaves.

title: pork chops 'n hominy
directions: Flour and season pork chops.
Saute onion in oil.
Brown chops in skillet only until slightly brown.
Place hominy in bottom of a shallow baking dish.
Follow with chops and onions.
Cover all with soup, diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: red and white freeze
directions: Crush cranberry sauce with fork.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into loaf pan.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar; blend well with mixer.
Add walnuts.
Fold in whipped cream and spread over cranberry mixture.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into wedges and serve on lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: heavenly delight frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients and add the dressing.

title: angel food cookies
directions: Mix together shortening and sugars.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients, coconut and vanilla.

title: layered salad
directions: Arrange in bowl in order given.
Top with 2 cups Miracle Whip. (If using mayonnaise, mix 2 tablespoons sugar with it.)

title: batter for veggies
directions: In a small bowl beat egg.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Dip vegetables in batter and fry in preheated oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: seafood strata
directions: Mix together bread crumbs and melted butter.
Place 1/4 of mixture on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place 1/3 of crabmeat-scallops in a layer on crumbs. Sprinkle with celery seed. Pour 1/3 of heavy cream on crabmeat mixture.
Repeat layering crumbs, crabmeat, celery seed and cream 2 more times.
Sprinkle last 1/4 of the bread crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix pork chops with the egg and bread crumbs and place into a frying pan and cook.
Using a mixing bowl, place mushroom soup and a little chicken stock together to thin out the mushroom soup to a gravy like substance.
I like to saute a little fresh mushrooms and add to the bowl mixture, then add some fresh parsley.
Place the cooked pork chops into a casserole dish and add the soup bowl mixture.
Place in a preheated oven, 350°; cook for 30 minutes. Mash potatoes and a green vegetable go well with this dinner. Enjoy!

title: gooney bird pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix butter, nuts and flour.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice English muffins in half, cut each into fourths and arrange on 2 cookie sheets.

title: double lime punch
directions: In a punch bowl, stir all ingredients together.
Makes 10 servings.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg or egg yolks. Sift together salt, baking powder and flour; add to mixture. Blend vanilla into mixture.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Mix half of cake mix (dry) with the butter, sugar, water and eggs until smooth.
Stir in rest of cake mix.
Stir in nuts. Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and bag of marshmallows.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes more until marshmallows are puffed and golden brown.
Remove from oven; let cool for 30 minutes.

title: china-egg flower soup
directions: Put cornstarch into a small bowl and gradually add water, stirring it with a fork until you no longer see any lumps.
Break the egg into another small bowl and beat it with the fork.
Pour the broth into a saucepan.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Add salt.
Give cornstarch and water mixture a quick stir.
Add to soup.
Stir with a spoon until thickens (about 1 minute).
Slowly pour the beaten egg into soup.
The egg will cook in the hot soup and form shreds.
When all egg is added, stir once.
Pour in bowls and top with scallion or parsley.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from hot pan.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: carol's fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off all fruit.
Save juice.
Add enough water to the juices to make 4 cups of juice.
Cook pudding according to package directions, using the 4 cups of juice instead of milk. When pudding is done, mix thoroughly with fruit in large bowl. Refrigerate.

title: easy pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into very small pieces.
Put in large Pyrex pan or other pan, about 11 x 14-inches or so.
Mix all other ingredients in measuring cup; pour over pretzels.
Use pastry brush to brush all over.
Bake in a 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir very often and rebrush!!!
Cool.
Can freeze well if you wish!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald the milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add cornstarch. Beat the egg yolks; add sugar.
Blend the milk and egg mixture. Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove, then add vanilla and 1/4 cup coconut.
Pour into cooled pie shell and refrigerate.

title: autumn pumpkin pie cake
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix and nuts evenly over top.
Dribble melted butter over it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape into loaf in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until center is no longer pink, turning dish after 6 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with remaining barbecue sauce.

title: hobo bread
directions: Blend water, baking soda and raisins.
Let stand for 2 hours. Mix together sugars, salt and flour.
Add the raisin mixture and blend well.
Put into 3 (1 pound) coffee cans and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes in the cans.

title: coffee kringle(kaffe kringle)
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm and dissolve yeast in it.
Add sugar and salt.
Beat in part of flour and 1 unbeaten egg.
Add rest of flour alternately with rest of eggs, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Melt butter and add along with cardamom.
Sprinkle a little flour over the candied fruit to separate and mix with raisins.
Add to dough.
Knead until smooth and let rise to double. Knead on floured board.
Divide in two and form into a long roll. Shape into a knot and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until almost double.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with sugar and chopped almonds.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 twists.

title: easy twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in thirds. Place in 10 x 12-inch baking dish or pan. Layer bananas over Twinkies. Top with prepared pudding. Drain pineapple and layer on top of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: cabbage rolls(bierocks)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, baking soda, walnuts and pineapple in a large mixing bowl, using a fork. Pour in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°. (Bake longer if using a metal baking pan.)
Cake will still be very soft. Remove from oven and top with frosting.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cook neck and giblets until tender.
Remove neck and giblets. Save giblets for giblet gravy.
Save stock for dressing.
In stock from neck and giblets, cook onions and celery for 30 minutes. While onions and celery are cooking, in a large bowl, mix other ingredients.
Then, add onions, celery and turkey stock along with enough stock from roasted turkey to make a soft dressing; mix well.
Have dressing soft, about consistency of cake batter.
Bake in greased baking pan in preheated 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Shred cooked chicken and set aside.
Melt the butter in a large skillet.
Add onion and saute until tender.
Add chicken, tomatoes and green chilies, garlic powder, cumin, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat, stirring until liquid evaporates.
Heat tortillas, one at a time, in 1/4 inch of hot oil for about 5 seconds on each side until tender.
Drain on paper towel.
Fill each tortilla with 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Dep fry until crisp.
Serve with sour cream and taco sauce.

title: cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and melted Crisco and continue beating. Add sour cream, salt, muffin mix and lastly, creamed corn.
Bake in well-greased oblong pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lumberjack beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Mix with sausage and beans and combine with vinegar, mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in 1 stick of butter. Combine all ingredients in large baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato sauce, water, cream of mushroom soup and chili powder; heat.
Line greased casserole with pieces of tortillas and layer with meat mixture and grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cracker spread
directions: Place cream cheese in center of tray.
Place drained, rinsed crabmeat on cream cheese.
Pour desired amount of cocktail sauce over crabmeat (about 3/4 bottle).
Surround mixture with crackers.
Ready to serve.

title: granny newman's fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in deep baking dish.
Pour into deep baking dish the mixture of flour, sugar, milk and baking powder (no salt).
Add fruit.
Never stir once you've added the fruit to the batter.
Bake at 370° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple or mexican fruit cake
directions: In large bowl, beat 2 eggs until light and fluffy.
Add pineapple, then add flour, sugar, brown sugar and baking soda. Mix well by hand.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Cook by directions on can.
Whip together the remaining ingredients. Spread on cooled crust.
Add grated onions, broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, carrots and grated cheese.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Have butter soft and beat butter, 1 cup sugar, eggs and sour cream together until fluffy and light.
Fold in egg mixture, flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Fill pan 1/2 full of batter and sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar mixture on top.
Then add the remaining batter and put the rest of the topping on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco flats supreme
directions: Rinse lettuce in cold water and drain.
Tear into bite-size pieces.
Brown onion and ground beef and drain well.
Add to meat, tomato sauce, cumin powder, chili powder and taco sauce.
Bring to a bubble.
Turn on low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Arrange tortilla chips on plates.
Next, arrange lettuce over chips.
Next, add mixture, next cheese, then sour cream and extra taco sauce (optional).

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat wok or large skillet.
Pour in oil and garlic.
Cook garlic until brown and remove.
Stir-fry meat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the mushrooms, bell peppers, green onions and bamboo shoots and stir-fry 7 to 8 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients together and pour over meat mixture.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes until thick. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken.
Chop onion fine and saute in butter.
Add mushroom soup, water, salt and garlic salt.
