Layer chicken in buttered casserole dish and cover with Chinese noodles and dot with bits of pimento.
Spoon part of sauce on top.
Repeat layers and end with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: apple-cinnamon pudding
directions: Slice apples into a 9 x 9-inch square pan. Combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Add egg and salt. Cover the apples with the flour mixture. Mix cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Sprinkle over the dough. Sprinkle 1/4 cup water and 2 teaspoons butter. Bake at 350° until apples are cooked and top is lightly browned.

title: baked millet
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart baking dish that has been oiled.
Cover with lid.
Bake at 225° overnight for a breakfast treat.

title: tortilla pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread tortillas on a cookie sheet and bake 4 to 5 minutes until golden brown.
Brown and drain sausage. Combine sausage and water with taco seasoning mix.
Simmer until reduced.
Spread each tortilla with 2 tablespoons salsa.
Add sausage, vegetables and cheese to taste.
Sprinkle with crushed pepper, if desired.
Bake at 450° for about 8 minutes until cheese melts.

title: eriko's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes (skinned) and carrots (skinned) in boiling water until potatoes and carrots are done.
Slice cucumber in thin slices.
Mix potatoes, carrots and cucumber in a bowl.
Put in mayonnaise, salt and vinegar.

title: gooie cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo, and egg and spread in greased 9 x 13 pan. Do not spread on sides of pan.
Cream cheese.
Add eggs and powdered sugar.
Mix together.
spread on top of cake mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes. or until slightly browned on top.
Do not cut while hot.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cut cookies in half.
Whip together softened cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add partially drained pineapple; mix well.
Place tops of mixture on cookie bottom.
Place lid on top.
Refrigerate.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer vegetables in a large bowl in order given.
Mix together mayo and sugar thoroughly.
Spread on top of vegetables and sprinkle with cheese on top.
Do not toss.

title: pecan macaroons
directions: Cream sugar and egg white.
Add nuts and mix well.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes at 275°.
Let cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: oven fried sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seeds, bread crumbs and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts in the soy sauce and roll in the sesame seed mixture. Place the chicken on a baking sheet that has been coated with no-stick cooking spray.
Also spray each breast after placing them on the baking sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes at 450° or until browned. Turn halfway through cooking time.
Do not over cook.
Makes 4 servings, 7 fat grams per serving.

title: mandarin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended. Bake in greased pans at 350° for 25 minutes or until done. Cool thoroughly.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once, stirring constantly until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.
Can be frozen.
To reheat, bake 5 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada de pollo - chicken
directions: Place undrained tomatoes, chili pepper, coriander seed and the 1/2 teaspoon salt in blender.
Cover; blend until mixture is smooth.
Add sour cream and cover and blend just until combined (set aside).

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook
carrots
in
salt water.
Drain.
Meanwhile, cook onion in 3 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in soup, salt, pepper, cheese and carrots.
Place
in
greased 2 quart casserole.
Toss bread stuffing
with
melted butter and spoon over top of carrots. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate date nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and set aside.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In another medium bowl, combine 1/3 cup sugar, chocolate and walnuts; set aside.
In a large bowl with an electric mixer at high speed, cream shortening and remaining 1 cup of sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla at low speed.
Alternately stir in flour mixture and water, just until blended.
Stir in dates.

title: crescent rolls with half the fat
directions: Combine oil, yogurt and sugar.
Set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt mixture, egg and egg white.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir 2 cups flour mixture into yogurt mixture; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Gradually stir in remaining flour.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine Raisin Bran, sugar and flour sifted with soda, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt in large bowl.
Add mixture of eggs, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Refrigerate in covered container. Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
May be kept in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: creamed onions with almonds
directions: Place onions in buttered casserole dish.
Combine soup with cheese and sherry.
Pour over onions; toss lightly.
(Can refrigerate at this point.)
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp and bacon bites
directions: Mix shrimp and garlic; pour chili sauce over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours, stirring occasionally.
Cut bacon slices into halves.
Cook bacon until limp; drain.
Wrap each shrimp in bacon pieces; secure with wooden pick.
Set oven to broil and/or 550°.
Broil with tops 2 to 3 inches from heat until bacon is crisp.
Makes about 16 appetizers.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat one minute after each addition.
Combine sifted flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, stirring just until well blended.
Stir in coconut and flavorings.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool completely. Yield: 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie tin or 8-inch round pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Surprisingly good.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Wait until you are ready to eat before adding bananas.

title: aunt mattie's maple joys (cookies)
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
At low speed, add flour, mixing well.
Set aside 1/3 cup flour mixture.
Add oats, egg, milk maple flavoring, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Shape to form 1-inch balls.
Stir ginger into 1/3 cup reserved flour mixture.
Roll balls in reserved flour mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: mock ice cream
directions: Heat marshmallows and milk until dissolved.
Allow to cool. Whip whipping cream for 2 minutes and add marshmallow mixture. Add vanilla and mix.
Pour into freezing tray and add Grape-Nuts. Cut Grape-Nuts through mixture with knife.
Freeze 2 hours.

title: cape cod fish chowder(low-cal)
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil. Add onion and saute. Add thyme and potatoes. Saute 1 more minute. Add water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add flounder and scallops. Cook, covered, about 8 minutes.
Combine milk, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Stir into soup and cook 5 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix enchilada sauce, tomato sauce, water and flour.
Simmer. Brown hamburger.
Grate cheese, cut onion.
Add onion, cheese and about half of the sauce to meat mixture.
Mix together.
Heat tortillas.
Roll up and put into baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup hot water. Add pineapple and cottage cheese. Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill this in an oblong dish, cut into squares to serve.

title: mock chocolate eclair
directions: Best to refrigerate, at least 24 hours.

title: millers green bean casserole
directions: Cut up onion and bell pepper; cook with ground beef.
Season to your liking.
Drain oil.
Put beef mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make instant mash potatoes (serving 6 people) as directed. Add sour cream and garlic salt; lay over ground beef.
Open cans of green beans; drain water and lay over mashed potatoes.
Open the tomato soup and lay over beans.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes. Enjoy it!
It's delicious!

title: spicy tomato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: lemon basil pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt in cooking water.
Drain and return to pan.
In a small bowl, combine butter, lemon juice, basil, garlic salt and pepper.
Toss with cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid; flake.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan or shape into loaf on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: near eastern coffee
directions: Dissolve instant coffee in the brewed coffee; stir in honey and spice.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Serve hot in demitasse cups.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon, if desired. Makes 6 demitasse servings.

title: cake won't stay around
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl. Make a well in center of dry ingredients. Add eggs, pineapple, nuts, oil and vanilla. Just stir a few times. Do not beat. Bake at 350° in a well-greased and floured tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool well before removing from pan.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes eight 4-inch pancakes.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted margarine, sugar and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: dirty rice
directions: For a more spicy flavor, use more Cajun spices; add 1/2 pound of ground beef; use "hot" sausage.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados; add remaining ingredients and stir. Serve on tortillas with shredded lettuce and cheese or use as a dip.

title: fried corn
directions: In medium skillet, melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add corn, sugar and salt; stir well.
Dot with remaining 4 tablespoons of butter. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.
Use 2 teaspoons of mix to each cup of boiling water to serve.
Yield: 30 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as usual.
Add to all other ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.

title: "roll kuchen" (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dough will be sticky.
Roll out and deep fry.

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, about 30 minutes or until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: In large container, toss together peas, Shoe Peg corn, pimentos, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Set aside.
In small saucepan, mix vinegar, oil, sugar, water, black pepper and salt. Heat marinade until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and pour over vegetables.

title: streusel cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix for 2 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, chiles, onion, sour cream and half of the cheese.
Set aside half of this mixture.
Add diced chicken to the other half and mix.
Place tortillas in a 9 x 3-inch pan.
Fill each tortilla with the chicken mixture.
Fold over each tortilla to seal.
Pour other half of soup mixture over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer chicken, tortillas, onion, cheese and sauce in casserole. Bake 1 hour uncovered.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Drain 1 cup juice from pineapple and discard.
In large mixing bowl,
mix flour, sugar and
soda	to
blend.
Combine eggs, sour cream, pineapple, oil,
vanilla,
lemon
peel	and lemon juice.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir
until	moist.	Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at
350° for 65 to 70 minutes. Cool in pan for 20 minutes.
Turn	out
on
rack
to finish cooling.

title: brownies
directions: Blend together.
Cook at 325° for about 7 or 8 minutes.
Keep checking; do not overcook.

title: pecan pie #5
directions: Beat well the eggs, salt and brown sugar.
Add white syrup vanilla, melted butter and pecans.
Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 370° for 15 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not open oven until done.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Bring to boil while stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add immediately 2 five cent Hershey chocolate bars and vanilla.
Stir and pour into pan.
Cool and mark into squares.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Press nuts into bottom of pie crust.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Mix cream cheese and sugar; mix Dream Whip with milk and vanilla.
Combine these ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Place berries on top.
Chill.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with salt into mixing bowl. Add milk, oil and egg white and beat until smooth.
Add water to make a medium thin batter.
Separate onion slices into rings and dip into batter so each ring is completely covered.
Drop batter-covered rings into deep fat heated to about 375° and fry to a golden brown.
Fry a few rings at a time.
Lift out and drain on paper toweling; sprinkle with salt.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat 2-inches deep oil to 375°.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into hot oil, frying a few at a time until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars until creamy and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in sour cream, blending well.
Sift dry ingredients with flour.
Add to batter with lemon or vanilla extract.
Add enough flour so dough can be easily rolled out.

title: spinach bread
directions: Add hot, cooked spinach to cheese/butter mixture. Spread on bread. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350 until hot.

title: budget hamburg barbecue
directions: Fry chuck or turkey, pepper and onion together; take off grease.
Mix egg with catsup, water, sugar, dry mustard and vinegar.
Add to meat mixture.
Then add corn flakes and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: casey's whole wheat bread
directions: Soften dry yeast in 1/4 warm water.
Mix together yeast, brown sugar, salt and 2 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Add shortening and wheat flour; blend well.
Add all-purpose flour, slowly.
When all ingredients are mixed, turn onto a floured board or counter and knead until smooth and elastic.
Dough should be soft.
Place in a greased bowl and turn dough over, greasing top of dough ball.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir well.
Combine buttermilk, oil and egg.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter onto hot griddle.
Turn when top is bubbly and edges look cooked.
Makes about 9 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: fantastic pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and beat well.
Stir in pecans just before pouring filling into unbaked 8-inch pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes or until the center is stable.

title: date pudding
directions: Bake in slow oven for 40 minutes in iron skillet.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: spanish rice with chicken
directions: Place chicken in large kettle.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour stewed tomatoes and water on chicken.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in uncooked rice, thyme, red pepper and garlic.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes more.

title: berry dips
directions: Mix half of whipped topping and orange peel in a small bowl. Mix remaining topping and cup of strawberries and yogurt in separate bowl.
Dip with whole strawberries, peaches, melon slices or cake cubes into mixes.
Refrigerate leftover dip.
Makes 5 1/4 cups.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine the vinegar, salt, dill weed and mayonnaise.
Pour over green beans, eggs, onion and pickle.
Stir gently.
Chill and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen corn
directions: Do not heat.
Mix and freeze.
Work as fast as you can and put in freezer bags.
You should have enough juice to cover corn in bag.
Cook as raw corn for table use.
I have tried this recipe for many years.
It keeps well.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Beat together egg whites and salt with electric mixer until frothy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until smooth and glassy. Slowly add Karo and continue beating until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla.
Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugars until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Stir until a soft dough forms. Stir in toffee bars. Bake 8 to 10
minutes. Store in airtight container.
Yields 6 1/2 dozen.

title: texas goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as per package directions; set aside.
In large skillet, brown ground meat and chopped onion. Add corn, beans, stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add prepared macaroni and cheese and serve warm.

title: simple pecan pie
directions: Mix together
and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Put crust in baking pan.
Let cool.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple with juice, then add the pie filling.
Pour into baking dish and chill until firm.
Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and vanilla, mixing well.
Spread over firm gelatin and sprinkle with pecans.

title: salsa
directions: Combine ingredients in 6-quart pan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; boil gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into jars; seal.
Boil in hot water for 15 minutes.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix broth, oats, green pepper flakes, onion, salt (optional), pepper and eggs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Divide mixture into two equal parts.
Place into two greased 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Makes 3 servings each.
(Wrap one pan of meat loaf in aluminum foil and freeze to serve at a later meal.
This may be frozen in the uncooked stage.)

title: heavenly angel cake surprise
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Drain pineapple well, pressing out excess juice with back of spoon.
Whip 1 cup cream.
Fold in pineapple, cherries and almonds.
Slice and reserve a 1-inch thick layer from top of cake.
Cut cake around outer sides and inner sides, leaving about 1-inch thick border. Remove inside cake with hands; break in chunks.
Fold into pineapple cream.
Spoon pineapple mixture into cake hollow.
Cover cake with reserved top.
Whip remaining cream with sugar.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mardi gras cake
directions: Blend butter, cream
cheese,
sugar
and
vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time,
and beat well after each addition.	Sift dry ingredients together and
add
to batter.
Combine 1/4 cup flour with fruit and
pecans.
Fold
into batter.
Pour into a Bundt pan which has
been
greased
and sprinkled with 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: cream cheese drops
directions: Drop
by
teaspoonfuls.
Press cherry in center, or put jelly in center.	Bake in a 375° oven until golden brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, water and chili powder; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff mixture with fork; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cornmeal casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with grated cheese (I use Cheddar cheese).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or about 25 minutes in microwave.
Sprinkle on more cheese just before finished baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; pull off bone.
Put in baking dish.
Add mayonnaise, soup, eggs, crushed up onion and celery.
Bake at 375° until you are sure the chicken is hot throughout.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place in bowl the broccoli, raisins, sunflower seeds and onion.
Make dressing of mayo, Sweet 'N Low and vinegar and pour over salad.
Add bacon just before serving.

title: milky way candy bar cake
directions: Heat candy bars, margarine and pecans until melted; cool. Combine ingredients.
Bake in four 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with any kind of frosting.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat on high for 15 minutes.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and some melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer the powdered sugar mix.
Then layer with banana, crushed pineapple (drained), Cool Whip, nuts and chocolate.

title: barbecued roast beef
directions: Place beef in bag and pour all ingredients over the meat. Cook at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Pour juice in a pot and skim off fat.
Add a little flour to thicken for gravy.
Best if you cook in the morning to serve that night.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat together the eggs and sugar until the mixture loses its granular consistency.
Add milk and melted margarine; mix.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder and add to liquid ingredients.
Mix until just combined.
Do not try to make it smooth.
Toss blueberries in a little flour to coat them (this keeps them from sinking to the bottom of the bread).
Add blueberries to batter.

title: hamburger tater tot dish
directions: Place meat, salt, pepper and onions in frypan.
Then pour into casserole dish.
Then pour soup over this.
Add peas and top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Real good.

title: rice casserole
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in the boiling water.
While cubes are dissolving, melt margarine in skillet.
Add rice and onion and brown.
Remove from heat and add green pepper, bouillon and mushroom soup.
Place in deep baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until thick.

title: gravy
directions: Mix, cook and stir.

title: veggie bars
directions: Cover the bottom of an 11 x 17-inch jelly-roll pan (a cookie sheet with an edge) with unrolled sheets of crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit.
Make sure there are no holes. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Cut up butter and place in bottom of pan.
Pour in batter.
Pour cooked fruit on top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce.
Dissolve jello in this.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: bacon and eggs(microwave)
directions: Cut bacon in half and place in 1-quart dish or micro pan. Cover with paper towel.
Cook in microwave oven, covered, on Full power for 1 minute.
Arrange bacon at edge of dish.
Break egg into center of dish.
Pierce yolk with knife or fork.
Cook in microwave, covered, on Full power for 20 to 45 seconds, or until egg is cooked as desired.
Season with salt and pepper as desired.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Dredge chops in herb seasoned flour.
Brown chops in a skillet.
Mix can of condensed mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water and pour over chops.
Simmer until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: garden gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and vinegar.
Measure 3/4 cup of the gelatin mixture and to it add 1/4 cup water.
Pour into mold.
Chill until almost set.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
A variety of things may be added to this such as marshmallows, well chopped assorted nuts, etc. Refrigerate a few hours to bring out the flavor.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix 1/2
cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Grease and flour 9
x
13-inch
pan.
Sprinkle
half
of
cinnamon-sugar mixture in bottom of pan.
Save rest for top.	Beat sugar, oil and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.	Pour half of batter over sugar-cinnamon mixture in pan.
Spoon 1 can pie filling over batter,
then add rest of batter and sprinkle top with rest of sugar-cinnamon.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat salad sandwich filling
directions: Cook the ground beef in boiling salt water until done.
Drain well and mix with the carrots, pepper and onion.
Combine with enough mayonnaise to make a spread.
This must be used at room temperature to be good.
Do not refrigerate.

title: mystery bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Pat evenly into well buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, mayonnaise, Durkee, salt and pepper. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread potato chips over top.
Spread almonds, then cheese. Return to oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in oats, coconut and butterscotch morsels. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: low-fat chili
directions: In a nonstick skillet, cook ground round, onions and green pepper, if using, until meat is well done and vegetables are soft. Pour mixture into a colander or strainer; drain fat.
Place under hot running water and rinse until beef no longer feels oily. Return meat mixture to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until slighlty thickened and fragrant, about 30 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste. Makes about 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.
Each serving has 4.5 grams fat total (1.5 grams saturated).

title: danish kringle
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt.
Cut yeast and shortening into flour mixture like pie crust.
Whip eggs and milk.
Add to dry mixture. Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day divide in 6 pieces. Roll 1 piece into a triangle or rectangle.
Spread 2 tablespoons of filling in center of the dough, leaving space at both ends. Place jam or fruits or chopped nuts.
Fold in thirds.
Pinch together.
Place on ungreased pans (cookie sheets).
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Add sauce and water.
Mix eggs and all cheeses. Layer sauce, noodles and cheese and end with sauce.
Cover with foil for 45 to 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes in 350° oven in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fast banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on package.
When it is thick, stir in Cool Whip.
In serving dish layer wafers, bananas and pudding; repeat, ending with layer of pudding.
Chill.

title: "liz's winey chicken"
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Add remaining butter; melt.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add mushrooms; cook until wilted.
Add chicken broth, wines, marjoram, thyme, bay leaf, curry and paprika.
Return chicken to skillet.
Cover.
Cook over low heat until tender (approximately 1 1/2 hours).
Serves 4 to 6 adults.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Heat cheese and milk until blended. Add sugar, pimento, vinegar and egg.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add mayonnaise. Refrigerate.

title: biscuits and beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain and stir in beans, salt, sauce, sugar and onion.
Heat until bubbly.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Place biscuits on top of meat mixture and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and green onion in 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium heat, stirring to form large, soft curds.
When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and Cheese Sauce.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Heat cheese in double boiler.
Mix rest of ingredients except crab.
Pick out bones in can of crab and add crab to mix.
Do not boil.
Put mixture in ovenproof casserole dish and heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Cover, chill.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pineapple heaven cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except icing. Mix until well blended.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Variation: Add 6 ounces artichokes.

title: spiced potpourri
directions: Combine and add to 1 quart of water and simmer in open pan. Let cool and store, covered, in jar in refrigerator.
Reheat on stove or in potpourri pots if you wish.

title: pig out cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and juice from oranges for 2 minutes. Stir in oranges and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: jodie's gooey cake
directions: Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese stew
directions: Brown meat in oil and pepper.
Add soup, water, onion and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add cabbage and shoots.
Simmer until tender.

title: company shrimp casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter. Add shrimp mixture.
Put in long flat Pyrex dish and cover with sliced lemons.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes at 375° or until hot.
It may be frozen ahead.

title: quick blender pea soup
directions: Combine in blender milk and peas, processing until smooth. Melt margarine; add flour and stir until smooth.
Add to blender with salt, pepper and onion.
Process again until smooth.
Pour into saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer until mixture thickens, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Stir in nutmeg.
Makes 8 servings.

title: camp stew
directions: Brown hamburger, celery and onion till hambruger is done. Add kidney beans, soup and 2 cans of water to celery and onions. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: favorite pie crust
directions: Mix flour and Crisco.
Add egg and water mixture.
Add salt. Roll on floured surface.
Makes 2 crusts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with sour cream, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: mushrooms and onions for hamburger and steaks
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Saute onion in butter for 1 minute. Add mushrooms and saute 3 minutes.
Increase heat to high, add wine and cook 4 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: nippy beets
directions: Melt the butter; add the honey, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the hot sliced beets and serve.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Add water, vanilla and syrup. Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: baked lake trout
directions: Scrub lake trout.
Surround it with sauce in an open pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350° or until skin starts to lift off.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Mix juice with mustard and mayo. Combine all ingredients.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Shred carrot.
Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: cabbage chowder
directions: Combine vegetables, seasonings and water.
Cook uncovered for 15 minutes or until tender.
Add milk and bring just to a boil. Add butter and serve.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in jar and shake.
Chill overnight.

title: party meatballs
directions: Mix all together and form into small balls.
Brown on all sides.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and cold milk.
Add pudding mix and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and milk mixture.
Sprinkle wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together oleo and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Then add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix buttermilk and soda.
Alternate with flour.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(This makes 3 cake pans.)

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a large saucepan. Over medium heat, bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add marshmallow creme and continue stirring until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts if desired.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13 pan.
Cool.

title: chicken pork chops
directions: Trim fat and bone from chops.
Dredge pork in mixture of flour, salt, dry mustard and garlic powder.
Brown with oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken stock and cover.
Simmer until the gravy is thickened, approximately 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, onion, margarine, eggs, salt and pepper in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle grated cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Return to oven and continue cooking until well browned, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamy potato leek soup
directions: Bring leeks, potatoes and chicken stock to boil in large saucepan.
Season to taste with salt.
Cover partially and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, until tender.
Season with salt and pepper. Puree soup.
Whisk in cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to make a crust.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip; spread on top of pretzel crust. Dissolve Jell-O in water and add strawberries.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour on top of cheese mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough canned milk to make stiff. Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, take out and roll out for pies.
Can use apples, cherries or any other fruits.
Fry until golden brown.
Take out and drain on paper towel and sprinkle with sugar.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Scoop out seeds, then mix oil, onion and garlic and cook.
Mix remaining using 2 tablespoons parsley, then fill zucchini.
Put chopped tomato and remaining 2 tablespoons parsley on top.
Bake until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, water and eggs until fluffy.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, nuts and chocolate chips into batter.
Spoon onto cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesecake dessert
directions: Mix in bowl. Save 1/2 cup. Put the rest in 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp and eggs in food processor.
Add onions, celery, parsley and seasonings.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency. Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Spread batter in greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes right side up.
Remove from pan.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cocoa and if desired, nuts.
Add to wet ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a greased 9x12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over mixture; return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread the melted marshmallows evenly over mixture using a knife dipped in water.
Allow to cool.

title: microwave tuna sandwich melts
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except buns, until well blended. Fill each bun with 1/2 cup tuna mixture.
Place 2 sandwiches on paper towel.
Microwave on High 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.
Repeat with remaining sandwiches.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add water, during a boil.
Cool.
Mix with strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: grandma's nachos
directions: Place tortilla chips on cookie sheet.
Spread Dennison's chili on chips.
Put can of Ortega chilies on top.
Grate Jack and Longhorn cheese and cover generously.
Top with sliced olives. Put in 350° oven until cheese is all melted.
May add sliced avocados, if desired.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix; drop by teaspoons.
Bake at 350°.
Can use any kind of cake mix.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter (tap side of pan to distribute crumbs). Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate and butterscotch pieces.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Sprinkle on nuts and press lightly into pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into forty 1/2-inch bars.

title: rice meatballs
directions: Combine rice with beef, egg, onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 c. tomato juice.
Mix lightly, shape into 18 balls, place in skillet, and brown.
Add sugar to remaining tomato juice.
Pour juice over meatballs in skillet.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Cover 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugars in large bowl until blended.
Add egg and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda in small bowl.
Stir into creamed mixture with oats, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned around the edges.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Boil zucchini in salted water until tender-crisp.
Drain and set aside.

title: pina coladas for two
directions: Blend all ingredients together.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill 2 well-greased loaf pans half full and bake on the center rack of oven at 350° for 1 hour. Cool on rack.
Remove from pan.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash, drain and drop mushrooms into salted boiling water.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Combine everything into a mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand, the longer the better.

title: fruit dip(make 24 hours in advance)
directions: Cook until thickened and creamy.
Chill overnight.
Stir in 1 large container of Cool Whip.
Serve with any tart fresh fruit, such as Granny Smith apples.

title: pork chop skillet meal
directions: In skillet over medium heat, melt shortening; brown chops on both sides.
Top each chop with onion slice and green pepper ring. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover skillet and turn heat to high until food steams or bubbles.
Reduce heat to low and cook 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Thaw potatoes.
Combine with rest of ingredients except corn flakes.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes on top.
Use large, flat Pyrex dish or 3 quart casserole dish.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in water for 3 or 4 minutes.
Pull flowerets apart.
Make a batter of the next 4 ingredients, adding just enough water to make the batter stay on the flowerets.
Dip cauliflower in the batter and fry in oil until golden brown.

title: banana nut raisin bread
directions: Cream sugar, butter and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
One half cup of any kind chopped nuts may be added to batter before baking.
Let cool about 20 minutes, then serve.

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large Dutch oven, stirring to crumble. Drain well and set aside.
Melt butter in same Dutch oven.
Add flour; cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes, or until smooth paste forms.
Gradually add water, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly, stirring occasionally.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Yields 13 cups.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine mashed strawberries, cornstarch, butter, sugar, lemon juice and salt in a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until clear.
Cool.
Fold in the whole strawberries.
Pour into graham cracker crust (you may use a baked pastry shell).
Top with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb kuchen with strawberry jello
directions: Pour rhubarb in crust.
Sprinkle Jell-O over the rhubarb.

title: jerre's king ranch casserole
directions: Crunch up about 1/2 bag Doritos on the bottom of Pyrex dish. Melt Velveeta cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes, and cream of chicken soup. Layer chicken, melted mixture and grated Cheddar cheese on top. Put in microwave on High for about 4 minutes (or until cheese is melted).

title: shaker pickles
directions: Fill a gallon jar with the sliced cucumbers and onions.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Put in refrigerator.
Shake every day for 6 days.
Ready to eat on the seventh day.

title: cookie fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and fruit cocktail.
Add Cool Whip, dry pudding, buttermilk and pineapple (with the juice).
Wire whip works good. Before serving, crush entire package of cookies and fold into fruit mixture.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: delicious christmas date cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and sprinkle a little over dates and nuts. Add applesauce, nuts, dates and last the dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Bake in 2 layer pans for 30 minutes at 375°.
Spread with fruit filling between layers after both are cool.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cover beef cubes with water.
Heat to boiling.
Add bay leaf and peppercorns.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 3/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove from heat, let cool, skim fat from surface.
Strain stock into large saucepan.
Add meat cubes and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Yields 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: lemon squares
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat margarine until softened.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt; beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Press dough onto the bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Sprinkle cutlets with salt and pepper.
Fry until browned. Place meat in casserole.
To frying pan, add mushrooms, onion and parsley; cook a few minutes.
Stir in and brown the flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over cutlets.
Bake in slow oven, 325°, for one hour.
Serves 6.

title: salmon and noodle skillet
directions: Combine salmon, 1/4 cup soup, crumbs, onion, parsley, lemon juice and egg.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 patties.
If using frozen vegetables, cook until tender-crisp and drain.
In hot margarine, cook salmon patties until brown on both sides.
Remove from skillet.
In the same skillet, combine remaining soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Stir in noodles, Parmesan cheese and vegetables.
Arrange salmon patties over noodle mixture.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: hamburger vegetable chowder
directions: Brown the ground beef over medium heat; drain off excess fat. Add carrots, celery, onion, barley, potatoes and water, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for about 1 hour until the barley is tender.
Serves 2.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well. Add chopped
dates
and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then 300° for another half hour.
Good with whipped cream.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix 1/2 package of taco seasoning with refried beans.
Spread that in a 2-quart oblong casserole dish.
Layer rest of ingredients, ending with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 20 minutes until warm and melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Stir in melted butter and mix, reserving 1/3 cup. Pat rest in pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Combine the cracker crumbs and oleo and line bottom of pan.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, oranges and bananas.
Save pineapple juice. Mix instant pudding into this.
Mix Tang into pineapple juice and pour over mixture.
Add nuts and marshmallows.

title: jello blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water well; add pineapple and pie filling.
Mix well and refrigerate until firm.
Combine together cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.

title: green bean mix
directions: Will also need pressure cooker and small amount of cooking oil.

title: cheese 'n chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin; cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining picante sauce and cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, salt and pepper to the eggs.
Stir this into the macaroni.
Alternate layers of macaroni mixture and 2 cups cheese in a casserole.
Top with the remaining cup of cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rich chocolate brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Spread in a greased 8-inch by 8-inch by 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients together.
Put nuts in 9 x 9-inch pan and cover with the first 8 ingredients.
Cover with last 4 ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cake will come to the top with the sauce on the bottom.

title: chicken noodle bake(great for potluck)
directions: Mix corn flake crumbs with melted butter.
Reserve for topping.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to mushroom liquid to make 2 cups.
Set aside.
Measure flour and milk in saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add bouillon cubes.
Gradually add 2 cups of liquid, stirring constantly.
Increase heat to medium and cook until bubbly and thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in cream.
Layer noodles, mushrooms, chicken, sauce and parsley in ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered corn flakes over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: picnic in a casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain off excess grease.
Cut each hot dog into 4 to 6 pieces; add to browned beef.
Add baked beans and cooked macaroni.
Heat in oven or stove top.

title: bacon cheese brunch
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Mix apples and sugar; spread in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomatoes. Add tomatoes when ready to serve.
Mix and chill.

title: the wurst works
directions: Layer ham, turkey and roast beef on a hoagie roll.
Heat in microwave.
Add mayonnaise, lettuce, tomato and onion.

title: sherry mushroom chicken
directions: Combine in paper bag, flour, paprika, salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Place each piece of chicken in bag.
Shake and place in buttered pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (about 1 hour). Combine sauces, chicken soup, sherry and mushrooms; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over baked chicken and bake 15 minutes more.

title: egg custard without crust
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Combine all ingredients. Pour into pan. Bake in 400 degree oven until brown and set.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Strain peaches and reserve 1 cup syrup.
Crumble nut mixture from rolls into large saucepan.
Add flour, lemon peel and salt. Stir in syrup from peaches and ginger ale.
Cook on medium heat until thickened.
Stir in butter and peaches and bring to a boil.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain. Combine the cream cheese, soup, milk, catsup and salt. Stir until smooth. Add to ground meat.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Place Butter-Me-Not biscuits on top. Bake at 375° for 15 to 25 minutes longer.

title: green eggs and ham
directions: Mix eggs in a bowl with shredded zucchini.
Chop ham into bite size cubes, then add to egg mix.
Pour into hot, lightly greased frying pan and cook like scrambled eggs (serves 4 to 6.).

title: holiday yam bake
directions: Drain yams; mash.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Add juice to yams; add sugar and butter.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger-cabbage bake
directions: Cook ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown.
Drain.
Stir in cabbage, onion, 2 tablespoons water, salt, caraway seed and pepper.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Make pocket in side of each chop.
Combine bread crumbs, onion, celery, corn, green pepper and poultry seasoning.
Fill each pocket with dressing.
Close openings with small skewers.
Rub with mustard.
Sprinkle both sides with flour and paprika.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Add a small amount of water.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Drizzle oil over chops. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Brown under broiler before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked ice cream cones-cupcakes
directions: Follow cake batter directions. Fill each cone about 2/3 full. Carefully stand the cones on a cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes or until the batter puffs up and looks like a scoop of ice cream. After cakes have cooled, frost them & have fun decorating.

title: kahlua dip
directions: Blend in a mixer the above ingredients, Great to serve with fresh fruit. Better if served chilled.

title: popcorn snack
directions: Combine butter, sugar, syrup and salt in heavy saucepan; bring to boil stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over corn and nuts, quickly stir until well coated.
Pour mixture into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake at 250° until dry, about 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, spread apart, cool and store in airtight container.
Yields 5 1/2 quarts.

title: simnel bread
directions: Beat butter to cream in warm bowl.
Add 1/2 of sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks to currants that were combined with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Stir currants, flour and citron peel to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Add remaining sugar.
Fold egg whites in cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes in 7 x 11-inch greased pan.

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 260°.
Reduce heat to low; stir in butter until melted.
Pour syrup in thin streams over corn in bowl, stirring until corn is well coated. Cool slightly.
Butter hands and shape mixture into 3-inch balls. Place on waxed paper.

title: hearty beef vegetable soup
directions: Melt the butter in a soup pot.
Add onions and carrots and cook over low heat, covered, until vegetables are tender and lightly covered, about 25 minutes.
Add parsley, stock and potatoes and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until potatoes are very tender, about 30 minutes.
Add dill; remove soup from the heat and let it stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Pour soup through a strainer and transfer the solids to the bowl of a food processor fitted with a steel blade or use a food mill fitted with a medium blade.
Add 1 cup of the cooking stock and process until smooth.
Return pureed soup to the pot and add additional cooking liquid, about 3 to 4 cups, until the soup reaches the desired consistency.
Set over low heat; add salt and pepper to taste and gradually stir in the grated cheese.
When all the cheese is incorporated the soup is hot (not boiling), serve immediately. Makes 6 portions.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place hamburger in casserole dish (raw). Sprinkle chopped onion over hamburger.
Pour celery soup over this.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: spicy cranberry punch
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice with spices.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes; remove spices.
Add remaining cranberry juice, orange juice concentrate and water.
Chill.
Add club soda just before serving.
Makes 8 servings, about 1 cup each.

title: mushroom baked pickle-steak
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Fashion into 6 patties.
Brown quickly in a hot skillet.
Place browned patties in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.

title: low-fat peach crumble
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add sugar, mixing until creamy. Fold in pecans and oatmeal.
Spread mixture on a cooking sheet coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: orange blossoms (muffins)
directions: Combine yolks and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to sugar/egg mixture alternating with water.
Add vanilla and fold in egg whites.
Grease small muffin tins and fill 2/3 full. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and dip (not soak) in sugar/juice mixture.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix in 1/2 cup of sugar, the spices and lemon juice.
Put in greased 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix rest of sugar, flour, salt and butter to make crumbs.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggs a la goldenrod
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Wooden spoon for stirring is a help.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and chopped up whites of eggs.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over buttered toast.
Sieve the egg yolks over top.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light; beat in egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly before removing from pan. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar, salt, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well.
Melt margarine in pan, then spread nut mixture in margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: teriyaki marinade for chicken or steak
directions: Combine in blender.
Marinade for 4 to 12 hours, refrigerated. Baste with marinade during cooking on grill.

title: jam thumbprint gems
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, whisk vegetable shortening and applesauce until shortening breaks into pea size pieces.
Add sugar and beat well. Add vanilla and egg.
Mix well. Add flour mixture to applesauce mixture. Blend until smooth. Mixture will be stiff.
Using flour coated hands, roll a teaspoon of dough into
a ball.
Place on cookie sheets 1-inch apart. Press thumb into center to make indention. Fill with 1/2 teaspoon preserves.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until light golden brown. Remove from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Place on cooling rack and dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 24 cookies.
Per serving contains 70 calories and 1.4 grams fat.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Toss together lightly the corn flakes and 1/2 cup melted butter. Do not thaw potatoes. Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with crushed corn flakes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 15 as side dish, less if meal.

title: spicy grits
directions: Pour oil in a pan.
When heated, put mustard in; cover pan until mustard splutters.
Decrease heat; fry onions, vegetables and ginger.
Add 2 to 2 1/2 cups of water and bring it to a boil. Add salt.
Simultaneously, in a different pan, fry (roast) the grits until golden brown.
Add the grits, while stirring constantly, to the first pan.
Cover pan and let simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.

title: fruit crumble
directions: Filling:
Slice fruit in a deep dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, 2/3 cup of sugar, cinnamon and ginger.
Dot with butter.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add hamburger and brown.
Stir in tomatoes, paste and water.
Add salt and pepper.
Let simmer. Meanwhile, cook mostaccioli noodles.
Add to sauce mixture.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Blend all the ingredients together in a blender.
Pour into small paper cups and freeze.
Place a plastic spoon or popsicle stick in each cup when yogurt mixture is half frozen.
Freeze thoroughly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove the skin from the fish if desired.
Crush the soft bones and miscellaneous with the oil and flaked salmon.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in a greased loaf tin and dot with butter and bake until firm and brown.

title: sinful bars
directions: Mix oleo and brown sugar; cream well.
Add egg yolk, salt, vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Bake 25 minutes until golden brown at 350°.

title: peanut butter cream pie(microwave)
directions: In medium mixing bowl microwave cream cheese (Medium) for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until softened, stirring once.
Add sugar, milk and peanut butter.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon filling evenly into crust and set aside.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough 1/8-inch thick on slightly greased large pizza pan.
Press around edges.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Blend cream cheese with Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit in rows on crust.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend for 1 minute.

title: mint hot cocoa mix
directions: Place candy in heavy-duty zip top plastic bag; crush candy with a mallet.
Combine crushed candy and remaining ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve; combine 1/4 cup cocoa mix and 3/4 cup boiling water; stir well.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Slice lettuce and place in bottom of bowl.
Layer green pepper, onion, celery and peas.
Add Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle sugar on top of layers.
Add cheese and bacon bits.

title: cathy's mom's chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Mix together all dry ingredients. Add milk to butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Add yolks and vanilla last.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into cooked pastry crust and chill.
You can also put crushed Snickers bars in bottom of crust.

title: ice box vegetable salad
directions: Combine all vegetables and set aside.
In a sauce pan combine sugar, vinegar and oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain.
Combine the other ingredients except crackers to make the sauce.
Combine sauce with broccoli and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle the cracker crumbs on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: savory chicken crescents
directions: Blend cream cheese with butter until smooth.
Mix in next 6 ingredients.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Spoon 1/2 cup mixture onto dough; pull up 4 corners together and twist the dough.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle crumbs on top (crumbs also can be put into mixture).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Blend together first 5 ingredients.
Blend together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to sugar mixture.
Stir in quick oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen cookies. Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.

title: *aunt esther's sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash sauerkraut well and drain.
Chop celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Keeps for several days in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp-cheese ball
directions: Boil shrimp for 3 to 5 minutes; drain and rinse.
Peel shrimp and chop.
Combine cream cheese, shrimp, horseradish, lemon juice, onion and liquid smoke.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball and chill. Combine pecans and parsley.
Roll cheese ball in pecan mixture. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add next 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Cook until bubbly.
Spread Doritos in baking dish.
Spoon mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese.
You will need a 4-quart baking dish.
Put a layer of meat, then the sauce, then noodles, then cottage cheese, then Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese, and ending with meat sauce on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Toss bread and margarine.
Thoroughly mix eggs and sugar and add to bread.
Add pineapple and juice.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold with ham or poultry or any time.

title: cashew hot dish
directions: Brown together hamburger and onions.
Cook celery and noodles together; rinse and drain.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Stir in the cashews the last 15 minutes.
This is a large recipe, but can be frozen.
Leave out nuts and add when baked.
Makes enough for 25 people.

title: almond toffee
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan.
Add granulated sugar and salt.
Bring to boiling foam over medium-high heat, stirring constantly.
Turn heat to low; stir for 5 minutes.
Add almonds and return to medium-high heat, still stirring.
Boil until almonds split (you'll hear them pop).
Turn heat to low for another 5 minutes.
Pour into sheet pan and sprinkle chocolate bits over the hot toffee.
Allow to melt and spread evenly over all.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds.
Allow to cool completely, then turn out onto clean surface and break into pieces.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine all.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Drain before serving with tortilla chips.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Arrange wedges, peel side down, in a shallow pan.
Mix ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, brushing occasionally with mixture.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with sugar and salt.
In a saucepan, put oleo, shortening, water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl, put eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to first mixture and mix well. Bake in greased and floured shallow cake pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: marcy's mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
In a crock-pot combine sausage, Mexican Velveeta cheese, soup, diced tomatoes and chopped onion. When hot, serve with Mexican corn chips.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Add milk and salt to eggs and set aside.
In a 9x13-inch casserole dish, alternate layers of cooked macaroni and grated cheese.
Cover with milk and egg mixture.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: sand tarts
directions: Once butter has melted, add remaining ingredients. This mixture will have to be molded by hand into marble size balls. Place on greased pan close together (they will not spread). Cook at 350° for about 10 minutes. Roll while still warm in powdered sugar. Excellent around Christmas!

title: one dish dinner(serves 6)
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Remove from heat.
Stir flour, salt and pepper into drippings.
Stir in tomato soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil; cook for 2 minutes.
Arrange meat and vegetables in gravy.
Pour in casserole dish; cover tightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: jimmie's chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add chili seasoning, lemon pepper, salt and onion.
Stir well.
Add mushrooms and tomato sauce.
Cook on low heat for approximately 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg yolks.
Beat.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, soda dissolved in 1 tablespoon warm water, flour, rest of buttermilk and lemon flavoring.
Beat good.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 or 30 minutes.
Line pan with waxed paper which has been greased and floured.

title: one crust blueberry pie
directions: Keep 3 cups blueberries aside.
Cook remaining berries with 3/4 cup of water and 1 cup sugar until soft.
Make a paste of 1/4 cup water, salt and 3 tablespoons of flour.
Add to cooked berries and cook slowly over medium-low heat until thickened.
Add hot mixture to uncooked berries and turn into pie shell.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: alaska coffee can bread
directions: You also need 2 (1-pound) coffee cans and plastic lids to fit.

title: cream puffs
directions: Boil butter and water together.
While boiling, add 1 cup flour; let it cool some.
Stir in unbeaten eggs.
Stir until all lumps are gone.
Drop on greased baking sheet.
Use one teaspoon for small ones or a good tablespoon for large ones.
Bake in a hot (450°) oven for 25 minutes.
Cut tops off to fill.
May fill with cornstarch pudding or small ones may be filled with salad, chicken or crab.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, brown sugar, sugar, zucchini, salad oil and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda.
Add salt, baking powder, cinnamon and raisins or walnuts.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Good warm or cold with butter, jam or cheese.

title: baked brie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place on top of 1 to 2 pounds of Brie cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old fashioned banana bread
directions: *Milk may be soured by adding 1/2 teaspoon vinegar.

title: chili verde pie
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook onion, pork, peppers, salt and pepper until brown.
Spread in pie plate.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over pork mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in two 9-inch layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Pam or grease 10-inch tube pan.
Melt chocolate.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream first 3 ingredients together. Add flour; mix with hands.
Pat evenly over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice-nut loaf
directions: Cook rice.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in oiled baking dish and bake at 350° to 375° until browned (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: *Do not use all of it.

title: john mazumii
directions: Cook noodles and
drain.
Cook
meat
and
onions until brown. Season
with
salt
and
pepper.
Heat
tomatoes
and celery. Mix with meat
and
noodles;
add mushrooms.
Add 1/2 cheese. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining cheese. Let stand 1 hour, then bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cut orange slices in small pieces using 1/4 cup flour as you cut.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Fold into mixture until well mixed.
Add orange slices, oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet in rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.
Very festive.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, syrup and salt and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn off heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts, if so desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat; pour grease off.
Add spaghetti sauce. Mix Ricotta cheese, 4 eggs, parsley and 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese in a separate bowl.
Put noodles in water bowl until tender (be able to pick up).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter cubes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place bread in bottom of dish and sprinkle with crumbled sausage.
Top with shredded cheese. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over cheese. Chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from fridge and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: coconut rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, coconut and nuts in bowl.
Stir in milk and rum.
Mix well. Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Drop from tablespoon into bowl of 10x sugar to coat.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Roll again in sugar just before serving.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle layers of graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in milk and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb-pineapple pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Add egg. Beat thoroughly and add rhubarb and pineapple. Bake 10 minutes at 425° and reduce to 350°. Bake approximately 35 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: liver with apples and onions(stove top)
directions: Dry the liver.
Saute onions in 3 tablespoons margarine. Remove onion rings and saute apples until they are cooked through, but not mushy (about 2 to 3 minutes on each side).
Remove apples.
Saute liver about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Place on platter and top with onions and apples.
Serves 4.

title: easy french onion soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add onion and saute until golden brown.
Add water and bouillon; stir for first 2 minutes. Let come to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat.
Add pepper and wine (optional).
Let simmer for an hour.

title: sauce for shrimp
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given.
Serves 6.

title: oven salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 2 logs (approximately 2 x 5-inch).
Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight (24 hours). Unwrap and bake in pan or on cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour. These freeze well.
Serve with crackers or use in sandwiches.

title: curry cheese ball
directions: Mix together:
shredded cheese, onion, cream cheese, tabasco. Form into a ball.
Sprinkle curry on outside of ball.
Pour mango-chutney over ball and top with chopped walnuts.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in baking dish.
Mix onions, celery and mayo. Spread over vegetables.
Melt oleo, mix with crackers and spread over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directions on box.
Spray 13 x 9-inch dish with Pam cooking spray.
Add a layer of nuts.
Follow with a layer of coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the nuts and coconut. Pour the cake mixture over this mixture.

title: potato and onion frittata
directions: Heat oil over medium heat until hot in frying pan.
Fry potatoes in one layer until golden and tender.
Remove potatoes with slotted spoon to plate.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions in pan about 15 minutes.
Butter pie plate.

title: quick macaroni, beef and tomato meal
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add seasonings; drain excess fat.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. Return to pan.
Add meat-onion-seasoning mixture.
Stir in tomato soup and tomato sauce; heat well.
Mix in cheese chunks or sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.

title: fudge nut pie
directions: Heat butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts. Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars, eggs and oil.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and mix in alternately with milk.
Add oats and chocolate chips or raisins or dates.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: potato salad and dressing
directions: Cook potatoes in saltwater until done. (I cut potatoes in cubes so not to cook too long.) Drain; let stand until cool. Add remaining ingredients. Then pour cooked dressing over and mix well. Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: fish in a flash
directions: Arrange fillets in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch microwaveproof dish.
Brush with melted butter or margarine or fresh lemon juice.
Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Turn the dish halfway around; microwave just until fish is opaque in the center, 2 to 3 minutes more.
Let stand covered 2 minutes.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in your selection, whether he be prune, peach or lemon.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour and hard and sometimes even bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well seasoned with smiles and smothered with kisses to taste.
Wrap in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of deepest devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: chili con carne
directions: Soak the kidney beans overnight in cold water.
Brown the hamburger and onion in butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add tomato, water, beans and seasonings.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook for 1 hour.

title: charlie's corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a well-greased and *mealed 8-inch square or 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, seasoning as desired with salt, pepper or seasoning salt.
Roll into small balls.
Brown in cooking oil in skillet.
When meat balls are done, mix soup and water.
Pour over meat balls.
Serve over rice.

title: zwiebelkuchen(german onion pie)
directions: Roll out dough on pizza pan.
Cook onions in butter until clear, not brown; cool.
Spread on dough.
Sprinkle with cumin, salt, pepper and bacon.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Fold egg yolk into sour cream.
Pour over pastry.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or more, until golden brown. Cool and slice.

title: country potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in chicken broth until done.
Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add to potatoes.
Then add half and half, milk and salt and pepper.
Makes enough for 12 to 14 people.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Let grated cucumber stand 1 hour.
After cucumbers are drained, mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Be sure vegetables are very fine.
Yield: 2 3/4 cups.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook sugar, butter and water on high heat in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly. Cook for 10 minutes (at least 290° to 300° on the candy thermometer) or until brown. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour in a thin layer in a buttered 9-inch square shallow pan.
Lay chocolate bars across hot mass and spread evenly.
While still warm, sprinkle pecans over the top.
Press nuts lightly into chocolate.
Cool candy thoroughly and then break into pieces. (Can place in refrigerator to cool.)
Keep in refrigerator.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits almost through the meat.
Insert garlic and onion slices into slits.

Place beef in bowl and pour vinegar over. Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours, basting with vinegar occasionally. When ready to cook, discard vinegar solution and brown meat in small amount of oil until nearly burned on both sides.
Pour coffee and water over roast.
Cover and cook very slowly for 6 hours. Season 20 minutes before serving.
Thicken gravy if desired.
May add Oriental cut veggies for last 20 minutes if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Remove skin from sausage and fry until browned.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
In a large bowl, combine sausage with all the other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serves 8. Freezes well wrapped in foil in serving size wedges.

title: potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes, add onion, cover with water and boil until good and soft, but not mushy.
Drain, add milk, parsley, salt and pepper to taste and butter.
Beat egg, add some of the soup to it and pour mixture into pot.
This soup should be quite thick.
If it isn't, blend a couple of tablespoons flour with equal amounts of water and add to pot.
Cook a few minutes to blend flavors.
Cut up hard-boiled egg and distribute pieces in soup plates.
Pour soup over egg, sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate
