directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
When you want a cup of hot chocolate, add 1 or 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Add marshmallows if you wish.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute first 7 ingredients in margarine.
With shortening and flour, make roux.
Add roux slowly to sauteed vegetables.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: You will need 1 small cookie sheet with sides.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and add sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Spoon over crust.
Spoon pie filling over crust.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl until very smooth. Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel banana and orange. Chop all fruit into bite-sized pieces. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and chill.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; place in a deep baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
In a saucepan combine cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups; heat until creamy.
Add soup to chicken and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick chicken ala king
directions: Cook chopped onion in 2 tablespoons butter in a large Teflon skillet.
Add softened cream cheese, chicken soup, diced chicken and mushrooms with liquid; heat until bubbly.
Add diced green pepper and pimento; simmer.
When ready to serve, add the diced, hard-cooked eggs.
Serve hot over biscuits, toast or noodles.

title: prunella cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding prunes last.
Bake in layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 2 cookie sheets.
Combine milk, water, oleo and seasonings in large saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Add flour, all at once, stirring vigorously with wooden spoon until mixture forms a thick, smooth ball that leaves sides of pan clean.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well with a wooden spoon after each addition until paste is smooth and shiny.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Drop by teaspoon 1 inch apart.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn off oven. Prick in several places with a fork.
Let stand in oven 5 minutes.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender.
Place in a saucepan.
Add 1 cup water and heat to simmering.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into bowl.
Chill.
Serve as an appetizer or a dessert.

title: pickled beets
directions: Add 1 gallon cooked beets and bring to boil again.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: tato flake cheese buns
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine potato flakes, butter, sugar, salt, cayenne pepper and boiling water with evaporated milk added to it.
Blend in Cheddar cheese, unbeaten egg and softened yeast.
Gradually add flour to form a soft dough, beating well. Cover with Saran Wrap and let rise in a warm place until light, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: can apples (for pie)
directions: Mix
all together and cook until thick.
Peel and slice 1/2 bushel apples.
Fill jars
half
full and pour some liquid over and finish filling	with
apples
and liquid.
Leave cool for a short time and cold pack for 20 minutes.

title: oriental beef and vegetables
directions: Mix the soy sauce, garlic and water and pour over slices of beef.
Marinate 30 minutes, turning occasionally.
Drain meat, saving marinade.
Brown meat in a large skillet or Dutch oven in 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Remove meat from pan and cook the green peppers, celery, water chestnuts and onions for a few minutes until tender-crisp.
Mix reserved marinade with tomato sauce and cornstarch.
Put beef and mixture into pan with vegetables and cook until sauce thickens.
Serve over hot rice.

title: st. mary's biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients by sifting together; add Crisco, and cut in thoroughly.
Add milk and mix well together.
Roll dough and cut out biscuits.
Bake at 450° until browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: walla walla onion casserole
directions: Saute
onion
in butter until see-through.
Remove from heat. Stir in rice and sour cream.
Spread half onion mixture in a greased
x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese.
Repeat
layers.
Cover
and
bake
at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover
and
bake an additional 15 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Stir warm water with other ingredients, blending well with whisk or wooden spoon.
Cover mixture loosely with plastic wrap and let stand at room temperature for 5 days, stirring at least once a day.
After 5 days, the starter may be refrigerated in a covered container for a week or two.
Be sure to open container regularly to release built up gases.
Use the starter in any sourdough recipe.
After using, it may be replenished by adding 3/4 cup plain flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar and 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Let stand for 2 to 3 days at room temperature before using.
Replenish every couple of weeks and stored in the refrigerator.
The starter will last almost indefinitely.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini in a little water until it boils.
Let simmer until tender.
It will shrink down to 2 cups.
Drain well.
Cool. Add rest of ingredients.
Put in pie crust.
Add top crust. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: blue ribbon coconut pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with a fork.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until golden brown, 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in 9x13 inch pan.

title: chocolate chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all but chocolate chips in mixer.
Beat 4 minutes.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together spinach, onion, garlic, salt and allspice.
Stir in mayonnaise and yogurt.
Take 1 loaf of bread and hollow it out. Break up discarded bread and other loaf into finger pieces. Place spinach dip mixture into hollowed out loaf.
Place on serving tray surrounded by bread broken into finger pieces.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce and margarine in pan.
Stir until melted and add sugar.
Stir together on large piece of wax paper dry ingredients and add 1/2 cup of raisins.
Then add to applesauce mix.
Stir in all batter.
Will be stiff.
Pour into 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg mcbrandon
directions: Butter or grease a skillet and place it on a medium-high heat stove.
Toast 2 pieces of bread or English muffin in a toaster. Cook an egg over-medium in the skillet and remember to break the yolk.
When the bread is done, put as much mayonnaise as makes you happy on the bread.
When the egg is done, place a piece of cheese on top, turn off the heat and place it on one piece of the toast. Place the other on top.
If you would rather have the bacon or ham McBrandon, cook some bacon or ham and place that on before you put the top piece of toast on.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: *You can substitute 3 tablespoons cocoa plus 1 tablespoon margarine for each chocolate square.

title: french toast supreme
directions: Boil together butter, corn syrup and brown sugar for 1 minute. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and put the caramel mixture in bottom. Slice French bread about 1 inch thick or use Texas toast.
Put slices close together on top of the caramel sauce.

title: tuna-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine macaroni, cheese, tuna, pickle relish and onion in a large bowl.
Stir together salad dressing, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over macaroni mixture and toss.
Cover.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed crescents
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Unfold crusts and pull off both plastic sheets.
Place crusts onto lightly floured surface and cut into
12 wedges.
Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, poppy seed and 1/2 teaspoon lemon peel at medium speed with electric mixer until
well
blended.
Spread each pie crust wedge with approximately 1/2 tablespoon cream cheese mixture.
Roll up to form
crescents.
Place
on
baking
sheet
and
bake 20 to 25 minutes
or
until lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.
Beat juice
and
remaining
sugar
and lemon peel and spread evenly over cooled cookies.
Makes 24 crescents.

title: white cherry chocolate almond bark
directions: Place white chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High for 1 minute at a time until melted. Be careful not to scorch. Drain cherries and chop. Add cherries, almonds and extract. Pour onto wax paper and spread out until about 1/4-inch thick. Allow to cool completely before breaking into pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix coconut and milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until starts to brown.
Remove from pan while hot.
Let cool before serving.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Blend well and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine apple filling, lemon juice and cinnamon in a bowl; pour over center of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: coconut fruit squares
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Combine milk, rind and juice in large bowl.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Spread half of mixture over crumbs.
Arrange a layer of fruit; spread on remaining mixture.
Arrange another layer of fruit on top.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in double boiler or in microwave until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell and chill.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Put into container.
Fill rest of container with whole milk. Stir. Freeze in 1 gallon freezer.

title: marinated vidalias
directions: Slice onions and separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar; heat and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over onions.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Makes a lot, serves 8.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and dry ingredients. Add coconut and oatmeal.
Sprinkle a little flour on candy pieces; stir and mix to coat.
Add coated candy pieces to cookie dough.
Dough will be very stiff.
Shape in balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° until browned on top.

title: holly clusters
directions: Melt margarine and add marshmallows.
Stir continually. Add vanilla and food
coloring,
then
cornflakes.
Stir until color is well distributed.
Drop
on
wax
paper and place red cinnamon drops on top to resemble berries.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: crab and cheese melts
directions: Cut muffins into fourths.
Add chopped crab meat on top.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Put in oven until brown and cheese is melted.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese, sugar and eggs one at a time. Mix and then add flour and flavoring. Bake in a round tube pan. Put in cold oven at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. May vary with different ovens.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened in mixer bowl of electric mixer.
Beat in sugar.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth. Fold in coconut, whipped topping and extract.
Spoon into crust. Garnish with toasted coconut.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts into medium-sized pieces.
Flour fruit and nuts with about 1/2 teaspoon of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs together and add to butter and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Add baking powder to flour.
Sift.
Add flour to batter.
Add fruit and nuts.
Stir well to blend.
Add flavorings; lemon and vanilla.
Blend into cake mixture thoroughly.
Pour into greased tube pan lined with waxed paper and large enough to hold the 5 pound cake).
Put into cold oven and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
After removing cake from oven set on cake rack and cool for 3 minutes.
Then remove waxed paper and place on cake plate. Return to cake rack and leave until thoroughly cold.
When cool, wrap well with several layers of aluminum foil and place in cake container.
Store in cool, dark place until serving time.

title: sassy sand tarts
directions: Mix oleo, powdered sugar and water.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into crescents or flat rounds.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Check at 50 minutes.
Roll in more powdered sugar while hot and cool on wax paper.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into greased loaf pans (3 small or 2 regular size disposable).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with glaze.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Drain.
Mix beef with all other ingredients.
Put in fondue pan.
Use bread to dip in fondue.

title: calamari con pomodoro
directions: Have squids thoroughly cleaned.
Cut into small pieces.
Wash well.
Pour olive oil in saucepan and heat.
Brown garlic and onion.
Add squids.
Cover; saute 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and sherry; cook 10 minutes longer over low flame.
Add tomatoes and parsley.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender. Serve very hot with Italian bread.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer first four ingredients in dish as listed.
Heat in microwave until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining ingredients. Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add dry mixture to the wet mixture slowly to blend. Beat 2 minutes.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into middle of cake.

title: hot chicken stroganoff salad
directions: In skillet cook rice mix according to package directions.
Add chicken and celery.
Blend sour cream, mayonnaise, milk and salt. Stir in chicken-rice mixture.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture heats.

title: white cloud potatoes
directions: In large bowl, whip potatoes while warm.
Add ingredients as listed.
Continue whipping until fluffy.
Place in dish that can be heated in oven or microwave.
Heat and serve.

title: fried apples(a tasty breakfast dish with eggs and sausage or bacon.)
directions: Fry bacon in a skillet until about half cooked, leaving the bacon and melted grease in the pan.
Add apples which have been cored and sliced (leave skins on).
Cook over medium heat.
When apples begin to soften, add brown sugar and stir.

title: chili for fiesta surprise
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until done, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: tinolang manok(chicken ginger stew with green papaya)
directions: In medium saucepan, heat oil over medium heat.
Saute ginger, garlic and onion for 1 minute.
Add chicken and saute until chicken colors change slightly.
Season with patis and salt.
Add water.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add papaya; cook for 5 minutes or until papaya is tender.
Add spinach; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Serve hot.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: In a flat 3-quart casserole dish, place a layer of asparagus. Cover with chicken.
Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Stir in all other ingredients, except almonds.
Pour this sauce over chicken and asparagus layers in casserole; sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugars and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt; the dough will be stiff.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto UNGREASED cookie sheet.	Bake until light brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
The center will be soft.
Cool slightly and eat.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together; pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baklava
directions: Mix walnuts, 1/2 cup granulated sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a bowl.
Melt the butter.
Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Peel off one layer of fillo dough and place in pan (may have to trim dough for an exact fit).
Generously paint dough with butter using a pastry brush.
Repeat until 6 layers of dough are in pan.
Evenly spread 1/3 of walnut-sugar mixture on top of dough.
Repeat dough and walnut layers, ending with 6 layers of dough.

title: open-faced turkey sandwich
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box. In pan melt margarine and saute onion, celery and mushrooms until soft.
Add cream of mushroom soup, chicken stock, wine, garlic powder and pepper.
Let simmer until gravy gets white and thick. If gravy is thin, add 1 teaspoon flour.
Add turkey (several slices thick) to gravy and heat through, turning occasionally.
On plates, put mound of stuffing, over that put 1 slice of white bread and add turkey with gravy.
Makes 1 Open-Faced Turkey Sandwich; quick and easy.

title: poppy seed bread(makes 5 loaves.)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, sugar and egg.
Slowly add enough buttermilk to make a creamy batter.
Next, stir in butter.
Grease large black skillet and pour in batter.
Bake in "hot" oven at 475° until golden brown.

title: date cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream Wesson oil with sugar.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs and add all dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and stick toothpick all over to make holes.
Cover with glazed frosting.

title: stir-fry broccoli
directions: *Add other cut up fresh vegetables if you like, such as celery, summer squash, cauliflower, green pepper or mushrooms.

title: iris's chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix. Place in casserole dish. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle 1/2 can of French fried onions on casserole and cook until brown.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix this all together real good and cover.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together slowly the jello, pudding and water. Heat to boiling either on stove or microwave. Stir as needed. Cool slightly. Slice strawberries into the glaze. Pour into graham cracker crust. Put in refrigerator to cool. You may top with whip cream if desired.

title: pineapple ham loaf
directions: Mix together ham, pork, eggs, bread crumbs, milk and catsup. Divide meat mixture into 9 equal parts.
Shape into patties.
In shallow 13 x 9-inch baking dish, form a long roll alternating 1 patty and 1 pineapple slice, starting and ending with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Prepare Spicy Glaze used to baste. Bake 1 hour longer, basting every 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with 1 crust; combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into crust; seal with second pie crust.
Brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: zuppa povera(from ciao italiano - mary ann esposito)
directions: Boil rice in 1 1/2 cups water and set aside.
Heat marrow, then add onion and celery.
Cook to wilt down.
Add the spinach.
Cover and cook down.
Add tomatoes and cook 2 to 3 minutes, then add chicken stock, water, tomato paste, salt, pepper and parsley. Cover, raise heat and cook 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Cover and cook until it comes to a slow boil.
Just before serving, crack eggs into soup and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Don't let eggs touch.
Gently scoop out each egg into serving dish and add soup.
Top with Romano grated cheese.
Serve with Italian bread.
Delizioso!

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice; add cream cheese and beat mixture until smooth.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour mixture into prepared crumb crust.
Chill 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: choucroute au champagne
directions: Place sauerkraut in a colander; rinse several times under cold running water.
Drain and squeeze out excess water.
In a large Dutch oven, cook the bacon.
Remove bacon and chop it into small pieces.
Add onion to the skillet; saute until slightly golden brown in color.
Add garlic.
Add the apple slices and stir well. Tie bay leaf and caraway seed in small cheesecloth bag.
Add bag to mixture in Dutch oven.
Add cider and champagne; bring mixture to a boil.
Arrange ham steak and sausage over the sauerkraut. Cover closely and cook for 1 hour over medium heat.

title: clam dip
directions: Smooth out cream cheese until soft.
Add slowly the clam juice until desired thickness.
Throw out leftover juice.
Add clams and onion soup mix; stir well.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: mee-maw's three bean salad
directions: Mix spices, sugar, vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Add beans, diced onion, pepper and celery, if used.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Wonderful leftovers.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt; let stand for 1 hour, then squeeze out juice.
Heat together celery seed, mustard seed, sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Pack into freezer containers and freeze.
(Skim off the mustard seed, after cooling, for looks.)

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Add peanut butter.
Fold 1/2 packet Dream Whip into first mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put remaining Dream Whip on top.

title: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and
margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; blend well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes or until edges are light brown.

title: dixie peanut brittle
directions: Stir together the peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl. Cook 8 minutes on High; stir well after 4 minutes. Stir in butter and vanilla; cook 2 minutes longer on High.
Add baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.
Quickly pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet; spread 1/4 inch thick.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Yields about 1 pound.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup salt and let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar, water, turmeric, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables. Heat to boiling. Simmer 3 minutes.

title: bean bake
directions: *Hanover; use all contents.

title: indian summer vegetables
directions: Cut corn off the cob.
In large cast-iron skillet, melt butter or bacon grease.
Stir in corn and onions.
Cut zucchini and yellow squash into 2-inch slices, then quarter each slice.
Add to skillet.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Quarter tomatoes and cut each quarter in half.
Add tomatoes, 1/4 cup water, salt, pepper and basil.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender, not mushy, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot, sprinkled with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix the cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt in large bowl. Beat egg in small bowl.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Add to cornmeal mixture; stir until moistened.
Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Drop cornmeal mixture by tablespoon into hot oil.
Cook until golden.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Place pudding mix in a large bowl.
Add enough pineapple juice to make a soft paste and pudding mix turns a bright green color.
Mix well.
Add drained pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Mix well until fluffy. Refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat sour cream in separate bowl.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla and sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Add sour cream mixture and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°. Cool in oven for 1/2 hour.
Do not open oven door until finished. Top with favorite topping.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cool then shred. Mix Ritz crackers and melted butter. Saute onion and celery together with butter. Spread 1/2 of cracker mix along bottom of 9 x 13 casserole. Mix chicken, soups, sour cream and celery/onion mix together. Pour over crackers. Spread rest of cracker mix on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: eggplant pancakes
directions: Combine 4 cups water and vinegar in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add eggplant cubes, cover and reduce heat, simmer 20 minutes or until tender.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Blend and form into balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Put everything in a large pot. Cover pot.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Stir, cover and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Combine molasses, sugar, shortening, egg, ginger, salt and baking soda.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour; mix well.
Add boiling water.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in 8-inch square buttered baking pan.
Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: best-ever lentil soup
directions: Mix all and simmer for at least 2 hours. Check on how thick you want it.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onions.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare broccoli to package directions. Drain broccoli and arrange evenly over bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and top with cheese. Then add cracker crumbs and pour butter on top.
Cook until brown.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix sugar, flour, margarine and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
(You may melt margarine in pie plate and will not have to grease pie pan.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in walnuts.
Add beaten egg, applesauce and oil.
Mix well.
Pour batter into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup to boiling point; remove from heat and add cheese. Beat on medium speed until well blended.
Soak gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Add to soup mixture and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Cool but do not let thicken. Add all remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Serves 9.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook onion in oil until clear.
Add beef and brown.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Add broth and cook until tender. Add potatoes and cook until done.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Using mixer, mix well.
Add chocolate chips with a spoon.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan (or tube pan).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. (Check cake, may need a few more minutes.)
Cool in pan or 30 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze, if desired.

title: never-fail custard pie
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla; add to scalded milk, stirring continuously.
Pour 2/3 of mixture into pie shell. Sit it on oven rack and pour in remaining filling.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put ingredients into blender and blend until creamy and smooth.

title: diced frank hots
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put 1/3 cup mixture in each roll and wrap rolls in foil, twisting the ends tightly. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Place on grill or in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot in wrapping. Serves 12.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix brown sugar, vinegar, salt, hot sauce and catsup thoroughly.
Heat in pan until mixture just comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool.
Grate cabbage.
Pour liquid over cabbage and mix well.
Let sit in refrigerator a few hours or overnight.

title: microwave salmon
directions: Place steaks in microwave-safe casserole.
Squeeze lemon juice over steaks.
Generously sprinkle lemon pepper seasoning over steaks and cover.
Microwave on HIGH about 2 minutes.
Turn steaks; repeat with lemon juice and lemon pepper.
Cook another 2 minutes. Check for doneness and serve.
If thicker steaks, may need a few more seconds of cooking.
Steaks freeze well and when heated in microwave, taste fresh.
Serves 4.

title: pralines
directions: Place graham crackers on cookie sheet. Melt margarine and brown sugar. Add nuts and vanilla. Pour over graham crackers. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: veal marsala
directions: Dust veal slices lightly in flour.
Heat 3 to 4 tablespoons of salad oil in skillet.
Saute quickly 3 to 4 slices of veal at a time, over high heat, until browned.
Transfer slices to a serving dish or casserole and sprinkle each slice with paprika.
Add more oil, if necessary and repeat process for remaining veal.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Coat a 5-cup decorative mold with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatine over 1/2 cup orange juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often, until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups orange juice and cranberry sauce until well combined.
Pour into prepared mold and chill 24 hours until firm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
De-bone chicken and chop into small pieces.
Roast pecans in oven for a few minutes...watching carefully to avoid burning.
Add pecans and remainder of ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and chill. Serve with sliced croissants, or on a lettuce bed with crackers. Serves 10-12.

title: snappy spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook thawed spinach 3 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add milk while stirring.
Add cheese; stir to melt.
Pour over spinach in the casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, oleo and sugar and press into a loaf pan (8 x 12-inch).
Cream the cream cheese and add eggs and sugar and blend well.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: miniature pizzas
directions: Flatten biscuits.
Add pizza sauce to each biscuit round, then add the toppings you want.
You may use 1 or more, then add cheese.
This is a good recipe for children and teenagers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and put in large bowl of electric mixer.
Beat until smooth; add cream cheese and beat again.
Blend in eggs, flour, parsley, chives and seasonings. Turn into a buttered casserole and spread slightly crushed onions on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: weight watchers chicken breast florentine
directions: Spray 10-inch skillet with Pam and heat.
Add onion and garlic and cook, stirring constantly until softened.
Add mushrooms and saute until browned, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in spinach, cheese, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, oregano and nutmeg.
Spread 1/4 of mixture over each breast, leaving 1/2-inch border on all sides; carefully roll chicken breasts crosswise to enclose filling and secure with small skewers.
Spray an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam and transfer chicken rolls to dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: In a large stock pot, place 2 cans of beef and 2 cans chicken broth.
Add cubed stewing beef and tomato sauce and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add the fresh cut celery, carrots, onions and green beans and simmer for an additional 1/2 hour.
Add the can of whole kernel corn along with the 2 cups of uncooked barley and simmer for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
The butter may be added, as it makes the broth smooth, but you don't need it if you ware watching cholesterol.
The soup always tastes better the second day.
This recipe feeds 8 to 12.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve with vegetable dippers. Makes 2 cups.
(I use boiled shrimp, chopped up fine.)

title: beans and rice
directions: Drain the cooked beans and mash 3 tablespoons to a paste with a fork, adding a little water if necessary.
Heat the oil and fry the onion, garlic and pepper until soft.
Add the tomatoes and cook for a further 2 minutes.
Add the bean paste and stir.
Add the cooked beans and uncooked rice and enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until the rice is done.
Serve hot.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.
Cooking time:
1 to 1 1/2 hours for the beans and 25 to 30 minutes for the finished dish.

title: date krispie candy
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the two sugars and cocoa.
Stir in the milk and butter; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring, until sugars dissolve.
Let boil to soft ball stage, stirring constantly as mixture scorches easily.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well until blended and slightly cool.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
I use a standard cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pink lace salad
directions: Melt marshmallows; pour into clear bowl and add crushed pineapple and Jell-O.
Mix well, then add remaining ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: cheesy cauliflower bake
directions: Clean cauliflower head; shred in a food processor.
Place in saucepan with water and simmer, stirring gently until soft.
Drain any excess water.
Add milk and seasonings to taste.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Mix until chips are melted and pour immediately over the hot cake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans and potatoes in dish.
Mix soup and water, then pour over beans.
Cook at 350° until soup thickens.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Microwave 3/4 cup chocolate chips in small bowl 1 minute. Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: broiled halibut
directions: Place halibut in baking pan.
Set oven to broil.
Melt butter and garlic together.
Place lemon slices on fillet.
Pour butter and garlic mixture on top of fillet.
Reserve some mixture to baste halibut as it broils.
Broil for 15 minutes.

title: ricks crabs
directions: Melt butter slowly and add beer, 4 bottles at a time, Worcestershire, 3 bottles at a time, sherry, 1/2 at a time, half can of Old Bay, cayenne pepper to taste and Red Hot to taste. Stir all ingredients and
cook 45 minutes. Add crabs, 3 dozen at a time. Add remaining ingredients as needed to taste. Cook until done. Cook 1 bushel of crabs. Remaining sauce may be frozen and used at another time.

title: shrimp and cheese casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Combine ingredients, except crumbs and butter; pour into casserole.
Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until fluffy (not stiff).
Stir in sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add pecans; stir until pecans are coated.
Spread onto pan and bake at 200° for 45 minutes (or until not sticky).
Stir every 15 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: cheeseburger and french fries casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix both cans of soup into meat, then pour in dish.
Lay fries over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Halfway through, turn dish around.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat, chopped onion and green chilies in large skillet or Dutch oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise,
sugar	and vinegar 2 hours ahead.
Add to broccoli (bite
size
pieces)
and	other ingredients.
Let stand another 2 hours before serving.

title: jamie's "moo, cow, moo"
directions: Put root beer in shaker.
Add 3 dips of ice cream.
Squirt in chocolate syrup.
Shake.
Pour in a glass.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and mixture boils.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until small amount of syrup forms hard ball in cold water.
Pour slowly over the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add the vanilla, beating until candy holds shape when dropped from spoon.
Pour into buttered pan and cut in squares. (I drop mine by spoonfuls on buttered surface; it's prettier.)

title: chicken and spaghetti in hot peanut sauce
directions: In a medium, shallow glass dish or stainless-steel pan, combine the 3 Tbsp. soy sauce, the 2 Tbsp. lime juice, 1 Tbsp. sesame oil and the garlic/ginger.
Add the chicken; turn to coat. Let marinate at least 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cake mix.
Add to rest of cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Combine and pour over crust, pumpkin mix, 2 eggs and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.

title: special broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Put broccoli in baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Gradually add mayonnaise and egg, stirring to blend.
Pour over broccoli.

title: carrot souffle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the carrots, butter, water, salt and chives.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until carrots are tender, about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and stir until mixed.
Slowly add the milk, stirring and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat in the egg yolks.
Whip the egg whites until they hold soft peaks.
Fold into carrot mixture.
Pour into a deep, buttered casserole (1 1/2 to 2-quart size).
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until puffed and lightly browned.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: sunshine casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese danish bars
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Layer 1 package crescent rolls onto greased cookie sheet.
Smooth cream cheese mixture over rolls.
Layer other package of rolls on top.
Brush on egg white.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: new hummingbird cake(reduced fat and calories)
directions: Mix all together well, but not beat.
Batter will be very thick.
Beat 3 egg whites and 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until very stiff.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour into oiled pan and bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 30 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool more.
Use cream cheese icing if desired or dust with powdered sugar.

title: mother's squirrel stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate up to two days before cooking.

title: sweet roll
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil. Cool to room temperature. Mix the yeast in small amount of warm water. Add to milk mixture. Add the flour. Let rise for 2 hours. Stir down. Add the baking powder, salt and soda. Add another quart of flour. Out in the refrigerator. Make out on a floured board and let rise for 2 hours. Bake in a moderate oven. Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks. This will make a large amount.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish, set in a pan of hot water, at 350°.

title: green chili wheels
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas in jelly roll style.
Chill and slice in 1/4-inch "wheels."
Yields 5 dozen.

title: single cheese cake
directions: Combine.
Beat high speed for 5 minutes.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in miniature (2-inch) baking cup.
Put 1 tablespoon of batter in each.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and put on desired fruit topping.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in a pan.
Add water to cover and simmer for 2 minutes.
Dissolve flour in 1/2 cup water and add to ground beef.
Simmer until thick.
Peel potatoes, cut up and boil for mashed potatoes.
Cook corn.

title: heavenly hash pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and fold in Cool Whip.
Put in 2 ready-to-eat pie crusts and set in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Set aside.
Cook the noodles a little less than directions state.
In a large bowl or pan, combine all ingredients and stir well.
Place in slightly greased ovenproof pan and top with Parmesan cheese if desired. Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6. Great make ahead dish.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: *While warm, slice and spread with cream cheese.

title: quick cookies
directions: Bring to boil in large saucepan first 4 items over medium heat. Cook 1 minute at rolling boil.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla. Mix well.
Drop at once by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening until it will crumble.
Put egg yolks in a 1-cup measure and fill with water to measure 1 cup.
Sprinkle in egg yolk and water mixture.
Make out into five equal balls, each ball making either a top or bottom crust.
Freeze in the ball or already made out in pie pan.
You are now ready for your favorite pie.

title: chicken stew with dumplings
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water; add salt if you wish.
Boil until chicken is cooked.
Remove chicken breasts from water and cut into pieces.
Reduce chicken broth to 2 cups.
Add soups and cook and stir until boiling.
Add peas and carrots and heat until mixture is bubbling.
Prepare dumpling mixture of 1 2/3 cups Bisquick and 2/3 cup milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stew, reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes, cover pan and cook 10 more minutes.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix and put in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: meat balls for spaghetti
directions: In a large bowl, crush garlic with salt and all other ingredients, mixing well.
Form into balls and put on cookie sheet; place in freezer until your spaghetti sauce is good and hot.
Then add meat balls into the sauce.
(You can freeze ahead by putting onto cookie sheet until frozen and then storing in freezer bags until ready to use.)

title: squash puppies
directions: Wash, slice and cook squash.
Beat egg.
Combine all ingredients and drop from spoon into hot oil.

title: my red ribbon plain ol' apple pie
directions: Mix and form 2 balls.
Roll out.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in salted water until tender.
Drain. Beat until light.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/3 of the cheese and bread crumbs for a topping.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and top with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, and top is light brown.

title: carolines' salt pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients except cucumbers together and let cool. Pack cucumbers in jar and pour cooled mixture over then.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Wash and shred lettuce into bite size pieces.
Cut cucumbers and peppers into bite size pieces.
Layer all ingredients, except bacon, putting mayonnaise on top.
Layer again, ending with cheese and bacon.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Mix well with a fork in pie plate all ingredients.
Press out in plate with fingers.
Flute edges.
If you need a top crust, reserve about 1/3 of dough before spreading out in plate.
Roll out on waxed paper for top crust.

title: chicken rice roger
directions: Flour and brown chicken in a little oil.
While it browns, put rice, salt and pepper in a greased 9x13x2 inch casserole and strew the grated onion about.
Put in the mushrooms, juice and all.
Arrange chicken on top, pour the bouillon over chicken and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toss bread with milk.
Add fruit and butter.
Beat eggs and spices together.
Mix into bread mixture.
Pour into buttered 3 to 4-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla pudding over top.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and egg.
Press into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over crust. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: stuff shells
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (drain).
Melt cheese in hamburger. Set aside.
Cook shells and fill with meat.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Add melted margarine or butter to flour.
Pour in enough milk to make the dough thick enough to roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: no cook cookies
directions: Mix all together except chocolate chips.
Knead.
Pack solidly in a buttered baking dish large enough so cookies will not be too thick.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler or over water.
Add about 2 tablespoons water.
Pour over top of mixture and place in refrigerator.
Do not allow chocolate to harden before cutting into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(I use low sodium soup and diet mayonnaise.
I don't use pecans and chips.)
I usually sprinkle paprika on top for color.
Bread crumbs may be used instead of chips.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Place the chicken in baking dish.
Over this, sprinkle salt, pepper and thyme.
Spread the chicken soup over chicken adding 1/2 can of water.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over; cook about 30 minutes longer.
Remove chicken from dish and spoon the soup over cooked rice.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Set aside.
Place cream of chicken soup, chives, half and half and white pepper in pot.
Bring to a boil.
(Add more or less half and half to desired consistency.) Stir in broccoli.
Serve hot.

title: grandma keithley sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients and milk.
Knead some more flour in; roll out and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.
Serves 36.

title: confectioners sugar cookies
directions: Mix and let set in a refrigerator 1 day. Roll and cut out cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Can be made in little balls with nuts and covered with confectioners sugar.

title: jeanette's crazy cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, cold water, salt, vanilla, oil, soda, vinegar, sugar together well.
Pour into 13-inch x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: baked smothered chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter and roll in flour, paprika and salt. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
Pour soup and milk mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake 50 minutes more. Remove foil last 10 minutes.

title: southern pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops and celery until tender in cooking oil.
Pour off drippings. Combine remaining ingredients and pour into a 12 x 8-inch baking
dish. Arrange chops and celery on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Let sugar, butter and milk come to a boil.
Add peanut butter and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla; beat until glosses look is gone.

title: pasta shells with corn and chicken
directions: In a large pot of boiling water (salted) cook the conchigliette until tender, but still firm 8 to 9 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into buttered 3 qt. casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mash sweet potatoes in
large bowl; add sugar, milk and butter.
Mix well and spread in buttered pan.

title: arabic bread(pita)
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in bowl; sprinkle yeast over sugar and water mixture.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients; work into a medium-stiff dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Form into small balls and roll each
ball into 1/4-inch thick circles. Cover with a tea towel and let rise again 15 to 30 minutes.
Heat oven and cookie sheet to 500°.
Turn circles of dough over onto hot cookie sheets
and bake for 2 to 5 minutes (just until they puff up).
Turn over and bake for a few seconds until light brown on the other side.
Cool and store in plastic bags or freeze.

title: finnish oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put 9 x 13-inch pan in oven while it heats.
Add butter to hot pan in oven to melt.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar and salt until thick and about tripled in volume.
Add milk, cottage cheese, flour and baking powder.
Then beat until well mixed.
Swirl batter to coat pan.
Pour egg batter into pan.
Bake until well browned and puffed high around sides, about 25 minutes.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie crust for 1 hour at 350° or 400°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Layer rice, then water chestnuts, then chicken in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour over layers. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Add pudding mix to cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool and ice.

title: london broil butter-wine sauce
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place steak on rack with surface 3 inches below heat source.
Broil 3 minutes on each side.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Add wine.
Heat until bubbling.
Cut steak diagonally into thin slices.
(This method cuts across the grain in such a way that it makes the meat more tender.)
Drop into frying pan.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove to hot platter.
Surround with border of hot, cooked rice.
Pour remaining wine sauce over rice and steak.
Serve at once.

title: never fail hot rolls
directions: Mix and let set approximately 5 minutes.
Let rise.
Make rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Will make two 9 x 13-inch pans of rolls.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and soda; mix well and set aside. Combine cola, butter and cocoa in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spread Cola Frosting over warm cake; sprinkle with nuts.

title: mexican cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Mix eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half in a greased black skillet.
Add a few jalapeno peppers and pour on beef mixture and sprinkle on cheese and pour on other half of cornbread mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer crackers and 1 layer of mix.
Add another layer of crackers, 1 layer of pudding, 1 layer of crackers and finally 3 layers of crackers and 2 of mix.
Set aside.

title: zucchini carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two loaf pans.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, fruit, marshmallows and nuts together with dry jello.
Place in serving dish and garnish as desired.
Any flavor jello and canned fruit can be used.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Grease shallow, 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine ingredients, except bacon bits.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with bacon bits the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine or butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in eggs and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in pan. Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes.
Fold ham slice in half and place on top of chicken.
Heat cream of chicken, half and half and Mozzarella cheese in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir occasionally until cheese is melted.
Pour over ham and chicken.

title: pesto rice
directions: Cook rice; drain.
Add pesto and pine nuts.

title: fried rice special
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Fry meat in oil until light brown.
Add onion; fry until brown. Lower heat. Add coriander, laos, shrimp paste and red pepper. Mix well. Fry one minute. Add soy sauce and shrimp; mix well.

title: weis burger
directions: Mix together like a meat loaf.
Make into patties and place on grill.

title: crab chowder
directions: Cook the crab meat and onion in the water until onion is tender.
Add the potatoes, salt, chives, Accent, pepper and butter.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.
Add milk and instant potato flakes. Heat to simmer. (Do not allow milk to boil.) Serve.

title: pear pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions or finely chop; pour boiling water over and drain. Mix all ingredients and cook 20 to 30 minutes, then can as usual.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients (except peanut butter) and cook over medium heat, stirring often. Cook to soft-ball stage (when a small amount dropped into a cup of cold water will form a soft ball between fingers). Remove from heat and beat by hand for 1 to 2 minutes. Add about 3 tablespoons peanut butter and mix quickly. Immediately pour into greased (buttered) platter or glass pie plate. When cool, cut into squares.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Wash and core large
tomatoes;
cut into chunks.
Place in a large kettle, one
that
will
not scorch, along with the chopped onions, carrots,
parsley,
sugar,
salt
and
pepper. Bring slowly to a
boil,
stirring often to prevent scorching; lower heat and simmer
for
minutes,
or
until thickened. Cool slightly; then measure three
cups
at
a
time
into
a blender, cover and whirl at high speed until smooth, about one minute. Pour into containers and freeze.

title: mom's orange jello salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water. Add sherbet. Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Pour in approximately 7 x 11-inch oblong baking dish.
When chilled and set, spread with Cool Whip.

title: pink sausage strada
directions: Cook sausage and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Arrange layer of cubes in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese and then sausage.
Repeat layers.
Mix remaining ingredients and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Pour over layers allowing milk mixture to seep to bottom.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Remove in time for casserole to reach room temperature.
Place in hot water.
Bake 3/4 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: delicious cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Punch holes in top.
Boil pineapple and sugar; pour over cake.
Spread pudding on top, then Cool Whip, then coconut.

title: pineapple bake
directions: In a casserole dish, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and pineapple; stir.
Add bread and stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Toss pineapple and cheese together in bowl.
In saucepan, put juice from pineapple.
Add cornstarch, egg, vanilla and vinegar and cook until thick.
Pour over pineapple and cheese.
Fold in.

title: black russian cake
directions: Spray or grease Bundt pan.
Pour all liquid ingredients into dry ingredients at one time.
Beat 4 minutes. Pour into Bundt pan. Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Cool for 10 minutes, then invert pan. Poke holes in top of cake so glaze can soak in.

title: salad
directions: Combine all vegetables. Separately combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper. Heat until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables while hot. Let set 24 hours in refrigerator to crisp.

title: green beans on the grill
directions: Mix butter, horseradish, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Dab this mixture over green beans and wrap in heavy-duty foil and put on grill for 20 minutes.
Remove and cut up 1 or 2 tomatoes into wedges and place over top of beans, return to grill for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Unwrap and enjoy!

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips.
Broil 3 to 5 inches from heat until brown, turning as you need to.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place wings in baking pan.
Mix melted butter and hot sauce; pour over wings.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, basting often. Makes 4 servings.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Cut angel food cake into three layers.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip together.
You may need to add a small amount of milk, so these ingredients will mix together. Then place the cream cheese mixture between the layers of the angel food cake on top.
Last, put the strawberries or cherries on the top of the cake.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Mix with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle mixture over apples. Place in a large paper bag.
Clip or staple shut.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Put on lowest rack in oven.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Remove from bag and cool on rack.

title: italian beef
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on top of stove until meat is very tender.
Remove meat from sauce and shred with fork.
Put back into sauce and bake 1 to 6 hours at 300°.
Serve on buns.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate flank steak for 6 to 12 hours.
Grill until done to desired taste (approximately 20 to 40 minutes).
Cut into strips at 45° angle.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pack
scrubbed,
uncut
young okra into pint jars with a few celery leaves, 1 clove garlic and 1 teaspoon dill seed (or head of dill) for each jar.
Make a brine of 1 quart water to 1 pint white
vinegar
and
1/4 cup salt.
Heat to boiling, pour over okra and seal in clean sterilized jars.
Let stand 3 to 4 weeks.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Bake cake in a 15 x 10 1/2-inch greased pan and follow cake mix directions, except use pineapple juice instead of water.
Then add enough water to make enough water that it calls for on cake box.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: del monte pineapple pound cake
directions: Thoroughly drain pineapple, reserving juice for other recipes used.
Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk; mix until well blended.
Add vanilla and lemon extract; fold in fruit.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch or 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 250° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until tests done.
Cool on rack 25 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve plain or dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: cheese - macaroni bake
directions: Boil macaroni; add Velveeta cheese mix.
Add sour cream; mix. Put in a large baking dish.
Add shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: summer strawberry and spinach salad
directions: Mix in bowl paprika, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, vinegar, oil and sesame seeds. Arrange spinach with sliced strawberries in salad bowl. Before serving, toss with dressing. Enjoy!

title: mystery pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add cinnamon and cloves. Stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each addition until blended.
Stir in rolled oats.
Pour the mixture into pie shell and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until knife, inserted in center, comes out clean.
During the baking the oatmeal forms a chewy nut-like crust on top.

title: low-fat chili fries
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and toss well. Arrange potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 35 minutes or until golden.

title: crab quiche
directions: Line pie shell with foil and bake at 450 degrees for 5 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 325 degrees.

title: eulane's potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into large slices.
Boil in salted water until done.
Mix while hot with remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar and egg and beat well. Stir in chocolate chips and set aside.
Blend together flour, cocoa, oil, sugar (1 cup), vanilla, soda, water and vinegar. Batter will be thin.
Pour into 8-inch pan, then drop cream cheese mixture over batter and swirl through.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients by shaking or stirring.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce. Drain well.
Add tomatoes, beans and olives. Wait until serving to add chips, cheese and dressing.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough in pizza pan.
Make glaze with sugar, juices and cornstarch.
Add cream cheese and spread on cookie dough. After it's baked and cooled, add all the fruit, one layer at a time, until all are used.

title: hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in Ranch dressing.
Spread over shells.
Top with ham, olives and cheese (thin layer; or other toppings, if desired.)
Roll shell tightly and cut in 1-inch strips.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add alternately with the liquids.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake in 350° preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Orange Frosting.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Beat all ingredients except wafers and pie filling.
Line cupcake liners with one wafer each and pour mixture in.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
To serve, top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 14.

title: fancy chicken breast
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast with garlic powder, Accent, pepper and parsley flakes. Melt 1 stick of butter. Pour in a bottle of ketchup, ground mustard and 1/2 bottle of cooking sherry. Heat, then pour on top of chicken. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Take out and top with a can of whole tomatoes and chopped green onions. Bake 15 more minutes. Serve over rice.

title: chicken with pasta and broccoli
directions: Blanch broccoli in boiling water and drain.

Heat 1 tablespoon of safflower oil in a medium skillet, then add onion. When it begins to brown, add hot pepper flakes and tomatoes. Cover, lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Add broccoli, basil and salt. Cover and simmer slowly until broccoli is tender, about 8 minutes. Add the olive oil.
Boil pasta in rapidly boiling salted water until al dente.

While pasta is cooking, heat remaining 1 tablespoon safflower oil in wok or medium skillet, then quickly saute chicken, tossing over high heat about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Do not overcook. Add garlic and cook another minute or so.
Add the chicken to the sauce.
Pour over the pasta and serve.

title: blueberry oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash blueberries; drain on paper towels.
In a medium bowl combine all but blueberries; mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a deep depression in the center of each cookie and fill with 7 to 8 well-drained blueberries.
Push dough from sides to cover berries and pat down.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until light brown.

title: cheeseburger skillet dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
In large skillet, brown the beef with onion and drain. Stir in vegetables, ketchup, water, mustard and garlic powder.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Mix in macaroni and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hula cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Mash out liquid from pineapple and drain on paper towel.
Mix with next 2 ingredients together. Put half of frosting on top of cake, then oranges, then other half of frosting.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Place the graham cracker crumbs in a small bowl. Melt butter and add to crumbs. Add sugar. Mix ingredients together and place in a spring-form pan; press to the bottom. Save a small amount of crust mixture to sprinkle over the top of the cheesecake.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until blended.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean; insert knife halfway between center and edge of pie.

title: easy italian casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook pork and beef; drain fat.
Add onion, Italian seasoning and garlic powder; cook until onion is soft. Add Manwich and water; simmer 5 minutes.
In large 3-quart casserole, layer half the meat mixture, macaroni and both cheeses. Repeat layers using remaining meat, macaroni and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: joann's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and put back into pan.
Add butter, milk, salt, pepper and 1 1/4 cups cheese.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Put macaroni into greased baking pan.
Divide bread crumbs in half, stir into macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and bread crumbs; broil for 1 minute or until brown.

title: enchilada meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, pork sausage, seasoning mix, egg and onion; mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs in a large skillet and brown on all sides.
Drain off fat.
Combine enchilada sauce, soups and cheese.
Pour over cooked meatballs. Bring to slow boil, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a greased baking dish.
Pour orange juice over apples.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and butter until mixture is crumbly.
Spoon over apples.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Empty green beans into 3-quart pot.
Add 3 cups of hot water. Cook about 20 minutes on high.
Add water if needed.
Add butter and almonds; cook another 25 minutes.
Drain before serving.

title: uncooked sweet pickles
directions: Step 1:
Wash cucumbers and cover with salt solution for 7 days, 2 cups canning salt to 1 gallon cold water.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Place in ungreased casserole dish and bake for 25 minutes at 425°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Pat uncooked ground chuck into casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion on beef.
Spread undiluted soup over beef and onion.
Layer Tater Tots on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator.
Best if let stand 24 hours.
Yields 1 cup.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saut chicken and onion. Add soup and Velveeta. When cheese is melted, add green chilies, pimentos and mushrooms. Stir in spaghetti. Pour into casserole dish and heat. This makes 6 servings and is 5 Weight Watchers points.

title: chicken roll-ups(feed mill)
directions: Mix together cream cheese, butter, 4 Tbsp. milk, onion & chicken.
Unroll crescent rolls and make squares with two crescent rolls pressed together.
Fill each square with about 1 Tbsp. of chicken mixture.
Roll up each square from corner to corner and curl to make a crescent shape.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 20 minutes (watch bottoms).
Mix mushroom soup, sour cream and 1/4 c. milk in saucepan and heat through.
Drizzle sauce over chicken rollups to serve.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Peel, cut and boil the potatoes.
Mash and season with salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix in sour cream and softened cream cheese.
Mix well.
Put in casserole and refrigerate until ready to use or overnight.
(Can be frozen.)
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can use low-fat ingredients.

title: baked brown rice
directions: Place all ingredients in baking dish and bake uncovered 1 hour at 375° to 400°.
Delicious and very easy.

title: dunkin cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes until brown on top.
Should be crispy.

title: orange punch
directions: Place 1/3 of orange sherbet and all lime concentrate into large container.
Mash thoroughly.
Add ginger ale, pineapple juice and iced tea, stirring together.
Add remaining sherbet in small pieces and float in punch.
Pour mixture over ice ring in punch bowl.

title: jonelle's apple brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!!!

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together the shredded carrots, raisins, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix, whip and blend well the Miracle Whip and 1/4 cup pineapple juice and pour over carrot mixture.
Stir well. Refrigerate.

title: geri morris' cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Drop 1 vanilla wafer into the bottom of a cupcake paper or foil tin.
Mix the remaining ingredients with a beater.
Fill the cups 2/3 full on top of the wafers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool and top with cherry pie filling.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, salt, spices and evaporated milk with pumpkin.
Pour this mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over all.
Sprinkle nuts over top, then drizzle melted oleo over all.
Ready to bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or longer until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: play-doh
directions: Combine ingredients in pan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until ball forms.
Remove from heat and cool a few minutes.
Add food coloring and knead into doh.
Store in plastic bags.

title: diet slaw
directions: Grate or chop cabbage and pimento pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat mixture until it comes to a boil.
Cool, then pour over cabbage mixture.
Store in covered jars in refrigerator. Will keep for several weeks.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine carrots and oil in a 3-quart ovenware casserole dish. Cover.
Cook in microwave oven 4 minutes.

title: rice consomme
directions: Place dry rice in glass baking dish.
Add beef consomme.
Chip butter on top.
Add water.
Cover and cook for 1 hour at 375°.

title: oysters rockefeller soup
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and add the flour, onions and garlic.
Cook until clear. Add the chicken stock and cream. Stir thoroughly. Remove from heat and cool a bit.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften; shred beef.
Mix all ingredients and mold into ball.
Wrap in plastic.
When firm, roll in parsley.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soups, chiles, sour cream, olives, onion, some of green onion tops and half of cheeses.
Set this aside. Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Tear 6 of the tortillas into pieces and place them in the bottom of dish. Spread half of chicken mixture on top.
Repeat with remaining tortillas and top with remaining grated cheese and green onions on top.
Sprinkle with paprika and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tex-mex special
directions: Mash avocados and lemon juice in medium mixing bowl.
Set aside. Combine sour cream with seasoned salt in small mixing bowl. Set aside.
In base of 9-inch pie plate, spread refried beans. Layer the avocado mixture, sour cream and tomatoes, making smaller circles with each layer.
Sprinkle with green onions and cheese. Top with ground pepper.
Serve with chips.

title: cranberry bark - microwave
directions: In microwave oven in microwave-proof bowl, cook chocolate on High for 2 minutes until almost melted, stirring halfway through melting time. Stir until completely melted.
Stir in dried cranberries and toasted chopped almonds.
Spoon onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour. Break into pieces.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add to softened cream cheese.
Mix in grated cheese.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped salted nuts.
Chill.

title: damn good chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter and oil.
Place in 9 X 13 pan.
Warm brandy and pour over chicken.
Lightly saute onions.
Mix onions with apple and pour over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: zarex jellies
directions: Combine water, sugar and Zarex in deep saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 bottle Certo.
Bring to full boil again and boil 1 full minute.
Pour into jars and pour wax 1/4-inch onto hot jelly.

title: sour cream vegetable salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine into a 9 x 13-inch pan; top with corn flake crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add bouillon, celery, carrot and onion. Cook until tender.
Add soup and milk.
Cook noodles and drain. Add to beef mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook slowly, stirring constantly to form a smooth paste.
Add vinegar, sugar and water; cook until thick.
Place beets in baking dish.
Pour sauce over beets.
Cover lightly.
Place in oven to cook with rest of oven meal.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Divide into 3 pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Butter pan.
Dump pineapple and pie mix in pan.
Spread cake mix over pineapple and pie mix. Spread chopped nuts on top of cake mix.
Slice oleo thinly and cover top and bake in 350° oven, about 45 minutes.
Chill and serve.
If top is getting too brown, put a sheet of aluminum foil over top.
It will freeze well too.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place sliced apples into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with the 1/4 cup sugar.
In a bowl, mix Bisquick, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit.
Dot the whole top with pats of butter.
Bake about 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Cook juice out of beans.
Simmer onion in butter and drain (saving butter).
In bottom of casserole, put beans.
Layer onions and 1/2 of the cheese.
Add soup, then rest of cheese and crushed crackers.
Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon tomato bites
directions: Cut a slice from top of each tomato; scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Invert tomatoes to drain.
Reserve pulp for soups or sauces.

title: old fashion dumplings
directions: Work together until fine and crumbly.
Add 2/3 cup water and work in.
Add another tablespoon of water or more if needed to make a stiff dough.
Knead well.
Divide into 3 pieces.
Roll real thin.
Cut in desired pieces. Drop one at a time into the broth of boiled chicken.
After adding the dumplings, cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: pastry mix
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Sift together sprinkling water over the mixture.
Mix with fork to make dough stay together.
Let stand a few minutes to make easier to roll out.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 (8-inch) crusts.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, then spread in bottom of a 9 x 13 pan.
Then top with lettuce, tomatoes, grated
cheese and olives if you desire.
Serve with taco chips.

title: geri's ham spaghetti
directions: Mix all together and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot. Serve with fruit salad or green salad and rolls.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Beat egg whites in small bowl with electric mixer until foamy white.
Beat in 1/4 cup of the granulated sugar slowly, until meringue forms stiff peaks. Reserve.
Beat butter, brown sugar, remaining granulated sugar and egg yolks in large bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Mix 1/4 cup of the flour with pecans and raisins in small bowl, stirring until nuts and fruit are coated.
Sift remaining 1 1/4 cups flour with baking powder, nutmeg and salt onto wax paper. Beat into batter alternately with bourbon until well blended. Stir in pecans and raisins.
Fold in reserved meringue until no steaks of white remain.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs; add salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually, then carrots and mix.
Bake 3 layers at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried salmon
directions: Mix ingredients and fry in pan with cooking oil until done.

title: dinner steak
directions: In large pan, place a large piece of heavy duty foil.
Place meat on foil and cover in order as listed with other ingredients. Fold foil tight all around so there will be no leakage.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
When finished, meat will be in a thin gravy base which goes good with potatoes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all, then spread on tortillas and roll jelly-style. Chill, slice and serve.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for about 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat with beater until bubbles appear.
Slowly add 5 1/4 cups flour.
Stir with spoon, making a soft dough.
Knead on board for about 5 minutes.

title: chicken with okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook chicken breasts in canned tomatoes, seasoned with onion, salt and pepper.
When chicken is tender remove broth and debone. Return to broth and add okra.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serve with rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well and store in capped jar.
1 or 2 tsp. in cup or glass.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dream whip cheese cake
directions: Whip cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Place cherry pie filling on top.
Place in 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: vanilla sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour a cookie sheet pan.
